00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,480
(Hong Ji Yeon)

272
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:21,390
(Shin Seung Yong)

273
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:34,470
(EXchange 4)

274
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:39,240
(Episode 20: So, It's Goodbye, Then)

275
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:56,519
(Min Kyung and Yoo Sik's date with ex)

276
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,060
- Aren't you feeling cold?
- No.

277
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:00,160
Are you hungry?

278
00:16:00,830 --> 00:16:01,830
A little.

279
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:04,160
We're matching colours.

280
00:16:04,730 --> 00:16:05,900
I know, right?

281
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:09,499
This shirt is really pretty.

282
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,570
I want it.

283
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:13,840
Many people tell me it's pretty.

284
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:18,379
Did you see me in the pink shirt?

285
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:19,680
It looked nice.

286
00:16:21,780 --> 00:16:22,780
Right.

287
00:16:22,781 --> 00:16:24,480
You can live without me now.

288
00:16:29,990 --> 00:16:31,690
How many times did you cry here?

289
00:16:32,060 --> 00:16:33,060
In the Ex Room.

290
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:37,060
I should have entered. I regret it.

291
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:38,260
Why?

292
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,430
If you had gone there, you'd have had a runny nose.

293
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,200
That's too much.

294
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:47,370
If I had gone there,

295
00:16:52,940 --> 00:16:55,380
I would have known how you felt a bit more.

296
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:00,080
Why are you crying?

297
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:03,990
Do you have a tissue?

298
00:17:06,020 --> 00:17:07,589
It's okay.

299
00:17:07,590 --> 00:17:08,630
Yes.

300
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,929
- It's okay.
- There's nothing but wet wipes.

301
00:17:11,930 --> 00:17:12,960
Do you want one?

302
00:17:13,660 --> 00:17:14,870
Why are you crying?

303
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:21,410
Why are you crying?

304
00:17:25,580 --> 00:17:27,510
She's precious to me...

305
00:17:28,010 --> 00:17:30,280
and I hope she doesn't get hurt,

306
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:34,750
but I could see that she was having a hard time.

307
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:38,090
Do you want a wet wipe?

308
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:40,929
No. I can use my finger.

309
00:17:40,930 --> 00:17:41,990
What?

310
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,300
It's annoying.

311
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,230
- Why?
- What?

312
00:17:48,470 --> 00:17:50,230
Why do you keep making me cry?

313
00:17:50,870 --> 00:17:51,940
Don't make me cry.

314
00:18:06,050 --> 00:18:07,080
Are you crying again?

315
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:09,990
I'm sad now.

316
00:18:10,690 --> 00:18:12,720
This could be our last date.

317
00:18:47,360 --> 00:18:50,390
After I came here, I really felt something.

318
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:54,530
What did you feel?

319
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,540
I wondered if we didn't break up completely...

320
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,870
but we were in the process of breaking up.

321
00:19:01,970 --> 00:19:03,640
Something like a process of breaking up doesn't exist.

322
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:12,450
If it were not you, I as who I am wouldn't exist.

323
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:27,030
How can I forget the times we spent together?

324
00:19:33,140 --> 00:19:34,439
They were together for eight years,

325
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,839
so she took their date for granted all the time.

326
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:38,879
Thinking this could be their last date,

327
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:41,149
she won't be able to be happy. Her heart would break.

328
00:19:41,150 --> 00:19:43,609
Seeing them together on the screen itself breaks my heart.

329
00:19:43,610 --> 00:19:45,650
- Yes, I know.
- Seriously.

330
00:20:07,470 --> 00:20:09,239
- I miss my mom.
- What?

331
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:11,180
- I miss my mom.
- Your mother?

332
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:20,650
Mom worried a lot.

333
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:21,750
Why?

334
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:23,320
She just kept saying...

335
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:26,590
that I shouldn't say something bad about you.

336
00:20:28,730 --> 00:20:30,490
She said you were not that kind of person.

337
00:20:33,430 --> 00:20:35,530
She kept saying it from the beginning.

338
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:39,240
She told me I should never say something bad about you here.

339
00:20:40,470 --> 00:20:42,240
She said there's no one as sweet as you.

340
00:20:53,380 --> 00:20:56,149
(While each of them is feeling sorry, )

341
00:20:56,150 --> 00:21:00,290
(they arrived at their destination in the forest.)

342
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:10,029
(Hakone Gora Park)

343
00:21:10,030 --> 00:21:11,070
It's beautiful.

344
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:16,710
Map of Gora Park.

345
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:20,180
Earlier...

346
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:23,610
- What did you do?
- I almost sprained my ankle.

347
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:25,950
It can happen here.

348
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:30,250
It's made of stones.

349
00:21:33,090 --> 00:21:35,330
Let's relax. Shall we have ice cream?

350
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:39,000
Ice cream!

351
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:42,500
- Is my outfit all right?
- Yes, it's cool.

352
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:46,470
It's so beautiful. Let's walk slowly, Yoo Sik.

353
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:55,010
It looks nice.

354
00:22:01,150 --> 00:22:03,320
- Lots of good ones on the menu.
- Yes. I love it.

355
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:05,790
I think I'll have this.

356
00:22:06,660 --> 00:22:09,389
I'll have a soft serve, vanilla flavour.

357
00:22:09,390 --> 00:22:10,430
One vanilla flavour.

358
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:12,600
One iced coffee.

359
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:17,870
What are you going to do if it melts all over?

360
00:22:17,970 --> 00:22:19,000
It's okay.

361
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:20,910
I'm going to eat it quickly.

362
00:22:23,670 --> 00:22:24,909
(Satisfied)

363
00:22:24,910 --> 00:22:25,940
Is it good?

364
00:22:31,650 --> 00:22:33,150
I haven't seen a water fountain for a very long time.

365
00:22:33,580 --> 00:22:34,590
I see.

366
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:40,520
It's so beautiful.

367
00:22:40,930 --> 00:22:42,290
Shall we eat this under a shade?

368
00:22:55,010 --> 00:22:56,140
It's hot!

369
00:22:57,470 --> 00:22:58,939
- Is it hot?
- It's hot.

370
00:22:58,940 --> 00:23:00,110
I should sit a little more forward.

371
00:23:00,410 --> 00:23:02,410
- Do you want to sit on this?
- Yes.

372
00:23:04,850 --> 00:23:05,880
Sit.

373
00:23:06,520 --> 00:23:07,750
- Is it okay?
- Yes.

374
00:23:08,620 --> 00:23:09,820
It's really good.

375
00:23:10,150 --> 00:23:12,460
- It's going to melt away soon.
- I should eat it quickly.

376
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:17,290
It got on your hand.

377
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,830
It tastes so delicious.

378
00:23:24,300 --> 00:23:25,740
- Is it that good?
- Yes.

379
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:31,080
I love it. I really wanted to have this milk soft serve.

380
00:23:34,280 --> 00:23:36,750
- You didn't have it here in Japan?
- No.

381
00:23:36,850 --> 00:23:37,850
Min Kyung.

382
00:23:37,851 --> 00:23:40,320
(She spilled the soft serve while eating it excitedly.)

383
00:23:42,820 --> 00:23:44,960
- Hold it forward while you eat.
- I think I should.

384
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:46,420
Be careful not to spill it on your shoes.

385
00:23:47,220 --> 00:23:48,330
Put your feet back in.

386
00:23:49,830 --> 00:23:50,830
Okay.

387
00:23:52,760 --> 00:23:53,830
It's delicious.

388
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:57,229
Can you have it a bit further in?

389
00:23:57,230 --> 00:23:58,740
What did you say?

390
00:23:58,940 --> 00:24:00,440
What do you mean? My hand?

391
00:24:01,670 --> 00:24:03,110
- It feels hot, right?
- Yes.

392
00:24:03,770 --> 00:24:04,939
You like hot weather, Min Kyung.

393
00:24:04,940 --> 00:24:06,380
Yes. I'm so happy.

394
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:09,509
They look so good together.

395
00:24:09,510 --> 00:24:11,180
How come they look so good together?

396
00:24:11,420 --> 00:24:13,180
- You know, it's...
- It's insane.

397
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,989
To me, these two are a good match.

398
00:24:14,990 --> 00:24:16,649
- I know.
- I mean it.

399
00:24:16,650 --> 00:24:18,389
He's way too used to wiping things for her.

400
00:24:18,390 --> 00:24:21,189
If I were her, I'd tear up when he takes care of me like that.

401
00:24:21,190 --> 00:24:23,660
They might actually end up together as CODE KUNST said.

402
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,569
Coffee? Tissue?

403
00:24:28,570 --> 00:24:30,570
Just wipe this part with a wet tissue, just once.

404
00:24:34,970 --> 00:24:36,870
Hold your ice cream more forward, Min Kyung.

405
00:24:38,740 --> 00:24:40,140
(Screaming)

406
00:24:42,350 --> 00:24:43,679
(Still cleaning)

407
00:24:43,680 --> 00:24:45,680
Stop spilling it. You're always...

408
00:24:46,150 --> 00:24:47,520
- Do you want to take the cone out?
- Yes.

409
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:50,450
- Do you want me to take it out?
- What? Yes.

410
00:24:52,460 --> 00:24:54,190
I'm going to go for one big bite.

411
00:24:54,290 --> 00:24:55,290
Okay.

412
00:24:58,300 --> 00:24:59,330
Be careful.

413
00:25:08,110 --> 00:25:09,270
- Is it good?
- Yes.

414
00:25:11,780 --> 00:25:12,780
I'll throw this away.

415
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,050
- Why? Did you spill it?
- Yes.

416
00:25:17,250 --> 00:25:18,480
- Is it because it's good?
- Yes.

417
00:25:25,890 --> 00:25:27,889
It was how Min Kyung was...

418
00:25:27,890 --> 00:25:29,659
when I dated her in the past.

419
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:31,030
She needed to be taken care of...

420
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:33,330
and she was clumsy.

421
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,440
Actually, that was...

422
00:25:42,970 --> 00:25:46,580
how we usually were as a couple.

423
00:25:47,780 --> 00:25:50,680
I spilled the ice cream, and Yoo Sik wiped it away.

424
00:25:52,080 --> 00:25:53,750
He brushed my hair back and all.

425
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,320
Like he usually was when we were dating,

426
00:25:56,550 --> 00:25:58,890
he acted just the same as before.

427
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:04,030
I like ice cream, so Yoo Sik...

428
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:07,200
bought one for me and from a distance...

429
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:13,770
came running, and that scene reminded me of the past.

430
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:20,440
So...

431
00:26:21,780 --> 00:26:24,650
because that scene was too familiar,

432
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:28,050
I liked it the most.

433
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:55,150
(Hakone Hibarino)

434
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:08,130
Go further inside.

435
00:27:15,970 --> 00:27:17,369
- It looks good.
- I know.

436
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:18,500
I love it.

437
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:23,140
They have grilled meat too.

438
00:27:23,240 --> 00:27:25,209
- This is sukiyaki.
- Sukiyaki?

439
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:26,280
I wanted to try this.

440
00:27:26,380 --> 00:27:29,050
Everything looks great. Which one shall I eat first?

441
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:33,220
Go ahead.

442
00:27:33,221 --> 00:27:34,279
We should eat together.

443
00:27:34,280 --> 00:27:35,590
These are shrimps.

444
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,419
- Shall I have this first?
- What?

445
00:27:39,420 --> 00:27:40,790
- Shall I try now?
- Go ahead.

446
00:27:42,390 --> 00:27:44,029
- You can go first.
- I will eat this.

447
00:27:44,030 --> 00:27:45,060
Okay.

448
00:27:46,930 --> 00:27:48,130
You like shrimps, Min Kyung.

449
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,470
- Is it good?
- Yes.

450
00:27:58,010 --> 00:27:59,279
Have this. Have my portion, too.

451
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,280
I should do so.

452
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:05,750
Do you like it?

453
00:28:06,850 --> 00:28:08,350
- Try the beef, Min Kyung.
- Okay.

454
00:28:10,420 --> 00:28:12,290
- Shall I put it there?
- You can just put it here.

455
00:28:12,660 --> 00:28:13,890
Thank you.

456
00:28:20,500 --> 00:28:21,500
What is it?

457
00:28:21,970 --> 00:28:24,940
It took too long until we could have a meal face-to-face.

458
00:28:30,970 --> 00:28:32,010
I know.

459
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:37,410
We...

460
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:40,779
went to eat grilled clams several times.

461
00:28:40,780 --> 00:28:42,589
Yes. Do you mean...

462
00:28:42,590 --> 00:28:43,950
- when we went to Oido Island?
- It was fun when we went there.

463
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:47,460
It was fun when we went to Yeongjong Island, too.

464
00:28:49,860 --> 00:28:50,860
Yes.

465
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,900
I guess the places we haven't been together...

466
00:29:01,170 --> 00:29:02,170
are Jeju Island and...

467
00:29:17,890 --> 00:29:20,090
I want to go to Nha Trang again, too.

468
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:32,040
What do you want to do first when you leave here?

469
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:36,110
What?

470
00:29:37,110 --> 00:29:39,080
What do you want to do first when you go back to Korea?

471
00:29:41,310 --> 00:29:42,380
I don't know.

472
00:29:43,380 --> 00:29:44,950
- When I go back to Korea?
- Yes.

473
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:02,930
What do you want?

474
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:40,070
Why?

475
00:30:51,420 --> 00:30:53,280
Why are you crying?

476
00:31:15,940 --> 00:31:17,040
When I go back to Korea?

477
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:21,680
When I go back to Korea,

478
00:31:22,650 --> 00:31:24,610
I want to go to a hot-pot restaurant with you.

479
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:29,980
Having a meal with her, face-to-face after such a long time...

480
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:35,520
reminded me of the past so much.

481
00:32:36,190 --> 00:32:37,849
I could definitely feel that I wasn't as good...

482
00:32:37,850 --> 00:32:41,660
as how I used to when we were dating.

483
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,999
I felt that I put her through too much,

484
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:48,330
so I felt so sorry.

485
00:32:52,670 --> 00:32:57,010
I think she must have felt that was mean to her.

486
00:33:18,130 --> 00:33:20,600
It somehow felt like our last meal together.

487
00:33:28,740 --> 00:33:31,840
Yoo Sik is the one who always makes me tear up.

488
00:33:34,710 --> 00:33:36,179
And seeing him...

489
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:38,980
fall apart like that in front of me,

490
00:33:39,480 --> 00:33:41,450
I fell apart as well...

491
00:33:42,950 --> 00:33:45,390
and it was really hard for me to watch that.

492
00:34:22,490 --> 00:34:24,960
I'm sorry for making you look like the bad one.

493
00:34:28,570 --> 00:34:31,300
No one did anything wrong, but I kept getting emotional...

494
00:34:32,740 --> 00:34:34,169
If you can't be emotional here,

495
00:34:34,170 --> 00:34:35,610
where else would you be?

496
00:34:36,470 --> 00:34:40,580
I think I made things so hard for you.

497
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:44,710
No.

498
00:34:50,720 --> 00:34:51,790
What are you doing?

499
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,890
Is it too big for you?

500
00:34:55,330 --> 00:34:57,090
The meat is too big that it makes me tear up.

501
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:01,460
I cut this for you.

502
00:35:09,770 --> 00:35:11,140
Stop crying.

503
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:17,150
I shouldn't cry, but I can't help it.

504
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:20,150
Stop it. Stop crying.

505
00:35:21,180 --> 00:35:22,190
Here. Wipe your tears.

506
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,850
- Goodness.
- Wipe your tears.

507
00:35:25,460 --> 00:35:26,460
Okay.

508
00:35:28,660 --> 00:35:32,130
Stop crying, I told you. Seriously.

509
00:35:33,300 --> 00:35:35,169
- Wipe them.
- What can I do?

510
00:35:35,170 --> 00:35:36,799
You keep making me cry.

511
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,269
How come you actually use it?

512
00:35:38,270 --> 00:35:39,270
Stop that.

513
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,310
Thinking back,

514
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:47,540
I don't think I tried to understand your feelings.

515
00:35:48,310 --> 00:35:50,680
It's just that I'm someone who's really important to myself,

516
00:35:51,050 --> 00:35:54,220
so I guess I didn't spend enough time focusing on you.

517
00:35:54,320 --> 00:35:55,320
I see.

518
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:57,490
The reason we broke up...

519
00:35:58,220 --> 00:36:02,130
is that we both had our faults. That's the truth.

520
00:36:04,530 --> 00:36:08,329
But I guess I wanted to believe...

521
00:36:08,330 --> 00:36:09,770
that I didn't do anything wrong at all...

522
00:36:11,530 --> 00:36:13,640
so that I could hate you more.

523
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:27,249
(The date with your ex has ended.)

524
00:36:27,250 --> 00:36:29,219
(Please text the name of one person, excluding your ex.)

525
00:36:29,220 --> 00:36:31,350
(If you choose each other, you'll get to go on a secret date.)

526
00:36:31,490 --> 00:36:33,260
- Did you read it?
- Yes.

527
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:38,400
- I guess this is the end.
- Stop crying. What?

528
00:36:40,660 --> 00:36:42,100
Stop crying, Min Kyung.

529
00:36:42,530 --> 00:36:43,870
I guess this is the end.

530
00:36:50,410 --> 00:36:53,280
Yes. It ended so quickly.

531
00:37:10,590 --> 00:37:11,730
On this show,

532
00:37:26,110 --> 00:37:28,680
I ended up hurting you a lot unintentionally.

533
00:37:36,750 --> 00:37:37,850
I'm sorry.

534
00:37:47,630 --> 00:37:49,969
I didn't mean to hurt you.

535
00:37:49,970 --> 00:37:52,240
I didn't want to act that way.

536
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:58,780
You're still too big in my heart.

537
00:38:02,450 --> 00:38:03,880
That's how I feel.

538
00:38:08,390 --> 00:38:11,419
It felt like Min Kyung was leaving things...

539
00:38:11,420 --> 00:38:13,690
to my decision.

540
00:38:15,590 --> 00:38:19,130
I worried about Min Kyung a lot.

541
00:38:21,870 --> 00:38:24,630
Stop crying. Drop it.

542
00:38:38,720 --> 00:38:42,620
No matter who it'll be, explain things well.

543
00:38:42,850 --> 00:38:44,150
Explain things well.

544
00:38:46,290 --> 00:38:48,060
Explain things well to me too.

545
00:38:51,960 --> 00:38:53,030
Okay.

546
00:38:58,330 --> 00:38:59,900
Shall we get going?

547
00:39:00,900 --> 00:39:01,970
Okay.

548
00:39:02,140 --> 00:39:06,540
(Min Kyung and Yoo Sik's date with ex ends.)

549
00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:25,259
The date with ex Min Kyung wanted so badly ended.

550
00:39:25,260 --> 00:39:27,360
- It's sad.
- It's so sad.

551
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:31,029
Toward the end, Min Kyung kept saying,

552
00:39:31,030 --> 00:39:32,939
