555
00:39:38,340 --> 00:39:40,280
- Today...
- During the ex date,

556
00:39:40,510 --> 00:39:42,749
- the conversation flowed easily.
- Yes.

557
00:39:42,750 --> 00:39:44,709
- I know.
- It wasn't like that before.

558
00:39:44,710 --> 00:39:46,179
We got a glimpse...

559
00:39:46,180 --> 00:39:47,449
of their past relationship.

560
00:39:47,450 --> 00:39:49,249
- I know. It's just...
- Yes.

561
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:51,719
Seeing them together...

562
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:53,189
was so sad.

563
00:39:53,190 --> 00:39:55,689
In the end, Min Kyung...

564
00:39:55,690 --> 00:39:57,829
apologised for the harsh words...

565
00:39:57,830 --> 00:39:59,999
she said in the past.

566
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,999
All along,

567
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:05,339
we saw how much Min Kyung liked Yoo Sik.

568
00:40:05,340 --> 00:40:07,939
She said many mean things...

569
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:09,709
because of that.

570
00:40:09,710 --> 00:40:11,939
Since it was the last date with ex,

571
00:40:11,940 --> 00:40:15,909
Min Kyung looked back on her past behaviour.

572
00:40:15,910 --> 00:40:17,609
It could be the very end,

573
00:40:17,610 --> 00:40:19,379
so she decided not to be mean.

574
00:40:19,380 --> 00:40:22,319
She spoke honestly...

575
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,750
instead.

576
00:40:24,390 --> 00:40:26,489
In the process,

577
00:40:26,490 --> 00:40:29,129
Min Kyung grew a lot.

578
00:40:29,130 --> 00:40:31,589
I can't predict what'll happen now.

579
00:40:31,590 --> 00:40:33,060
- Only one day remains.
- I know.

580
00:40:34,060 --> 00:40:36,770
I can't stop crying.

581
00:40:38,570 --> 00:40:39,840
The weather is nice.

582
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:42,970
How does it feel to come to the sea?

583
00:40:43,370 --> 00:40:45,210
- It's nice, but...
- Is it nice?

584
00:40:46,740 --> 00:40:48,440
It feels strange.

585
00:40:48,750 --> 00:40:51,680
I know. We haven't travelled this far together.

586
00:40:54,650 --> 00:40:56,649
We wore nice clothes today.

587
00:40:56,650 --> 00:40:58,119
I know. You look very pretty.

588
00:40:58,120 --> 00:40:59,189
- I do?
- The light denim...

589
00:40:59,190 --> 00:41:01,760
- goes well with your brown hair.
- Really?

590
00:41:01,930 --> 00:41:03,890
Thanks. You can keep going.

591
00:41:04,690 --> 00:41:05,760
I'll stop.

592
00:41:06,830 --> 00:41:07,900
I'll stop.

593
00:41:08,200 --> 00:41:10,370
I can't believe I'm joking around with you.

594
00:41:12,270 --> 00:41:13,600
It's so fascinating.

595
00:41:13,970 --> 00:41:16,110
- You never know what'll happen.
- I know.

596
00:41:18,470 --> 00:41:20,810
Yun Nyeong has always liked a place like that.

597
00:41:21,040 --> 00:41:22,950
I should've taken her to such places often.

598
00:41:24,250 --> 00:41:27,320
I thought, "Why didn't I do that back then?"

599
00:41:27,880 --> 00:41:30,619
It was nice to hang out with her at a nice place...

600
00:41:30,620 --> 00:41:32,290
for the last time.

601
00:41:36,430 --> 00:41:38,360
- Do the photos look good?
- Yes, you look pretty.

602
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:41,030
- Really?
- Yes.

603
00:41:41,100 --> 00:41:42,900
It's so nice.

604
00:41:43,870 --> 00:41:45,030
Shall we take a selfie together?

605
00:41:45,300 --> 00:41:46,570
Do this.

606
00:41:49,470 --> 00:41:50,640
What was that?

607
00:41:51,370 --> 00:41:52,809
Why do you look so awkward?

608
00:41:52,810 --> 00:41:55,080
I feel awkward about taking a photo with you.

609
00:41:57,150 --> 00:41:58,819
- We used to wink a lot.
- Let's...

610
00:41:58,820 --> 00:42:01,720
take another selfie that shows our dimples.

611
00:42:02,420 --> 00:42:04,689
Back in the day, I thought we resembled each other a lot...

612
00:42:04,690 --> 00:42:05,960
when we took selfies.

613
00:42:06,590 --> 00:42:08,520
We had similar vibes.

614
00:42:08,930 --> 00:42:11,260
Now, we look so different.

615
00:42:11,960 --> 00:42:13,700
Many years have passed.

616
00:42:14,030 --> 00:42:15,569
We've changed a lot.

617
00:42:15,570 --> 00:42:16,630
Shall we go?

618
00:42:17,930 --> 00:42:19,070
I don't want to go.

619
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:21,800
Let's go.

620
00:42:25,110 --> 00:42:26,810
- Let's go.
- I'll lead the way.

621
00:42:26,910 --> 00:42:29,850
Okay. You lead the way.

622
00:42:30,810 --> 00:42:32,179
Step on the white spots with no moss.

623
00:42:32,180 --> 00:42:34,149
- Okay.
- Step on the spots I stepped on.

624
00:42:34,150 --> 00:42:35,220
Okay.

625
00:42:36,890 --> 00:42:37,890
What?

626
00:42:39,120 --> 00:42:40,190
What?

627
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:42,389
(Cafe Bar Magokoro)

628
00:42:42,390 --> 00:42:44,789
The atmosphere is so unique.

629
00:42:44,790 --> 00:42:45,830
It's very Japanese.

630
00:42:51,070 --> 00:42:53,840
How pretty. It looks tasty.

631
00:42:56,370 --> 00:42:57,740
It's a proper meal.

632
00:43:02,550 --> 00:43:03,909
What's this? Try it.

633
00:43:03,910 --> 00:43:05,380
I'll try it. Hold on.

634
00:43:07,580 --> 00:43:08,720
It's so tasty.

635
00:43:10,450 --> 00:43:11,649
It's like a fish cutlet.

636
00:43:11,650 --> 00:43:13,320
- That sounds delicious.
- That's what it tastes like.

637
00:43:16,060 --> 00:43:18,659
I'm not joking when I say this. I can eat the whole thing again.

638
00:43:18,660 --> 00:43:19,700
Really?

639
00:43:20,460 --> 00:43:22,770
Eat some more. Do you want to eat some more?

640
00:43:24,030 --> 00:43:25,070
I'll suppress the urge.

641
00:43:25,470 --> 00:43:26,470
Why?

642
00:43:29,040 --> 00:43:30,069
You can eat more.

643
00:43:30,070 --> 00:43:32,340
It's okay. I don't think I'll be able to finish it alone.

644
00:43:33,410 --> 00:43:34,510
That's so funny.

645
00:43:35,010 --> 00:43:36,410
You emptied the plates.

646
00:43:38,710 --> 00:43:40,019
Do you want some of mine? Go ahead.

647
00:43:40,020 --> 00:43:42,049
No, it's okay.

648
00:43:42,050 --> 00:43:43,320
- It's okay.
- I'm full.

649
00:43:43,650 --> 00:43:45,149
- I won't be able to finish it.
- Really?

650
00:43:45,150 --> 00:43:46,890
(Jae Hyeong gives her his side dish.)

651
00:43:50,290 --> 00:43:51,689
- Do you want rice?
- What?

652
00:43:51,690 --> 00:43:52,799
- Do you want rice?
- It's okay.

653
00:43:52,800 --> 00:43:53,900
I'm not going to eat it.

654
00:43:55,060 --> 00:43:56,070
Eat it.

655
00:43:56,370 --> 00:43:58,470
I feel like a pig.

656
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:01,870
I don't have anything left on my tray.

657
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:07,480
What's wrong with me?

658
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:12,220
I didn't know that Yun Nyeong ate so much.

659
00:44:13,450 --> 00:44:15,279
I wasn't even halfway done...

660
00:44:15,280 --> 00:44:17,550
