661
00:44:17,620 --> 00:44:19,090
So I gave her some of my food.

662
00:44:20,160 --> 00:44:21,790
Now, things are very comfortable between us.

663
00:44:22,530 --> 00:44:26,430
I think it's the relationship I hoped for.

664
00:44:29,370 --> 00:44:31,030
It's nice to say goodbye.

665
00:44:35,940 --> 00:44:38,139
(The date with ex has ended.)

666
00:44:38,140 --> 00:44:40,239
(Please text the name of one person, excluding your ex.)

667
00:44:40,240 --> 00:44:42,410
(If you choose each other, you’ll get to go on a secret date.)

668
00:44:50,690 --> 00:44:53,590
I wanted to tell you that I had always rooted for you.

669
00:44:57,390 --> 00:44:58,460
I wanted to thank you.

670
00:45:01,930 --> 00:45:04,800
Me too. I want to thank you.

671
00:45:05,770 --> 00:45:06,970
It's not the past tense.

672
00:45:10,270 --> 00:45:14,440
Had I not come here, we wouldn't have made up.

673
00:45:15,140 --> 00:45:18,750
We came here, made up, went on a date,

674
00:45:19,380 --> 00:45:20,680
and cleared a misunderstanding.

675
00:45:21,220 --> 00:45:23,849
What makes me the happiest about joining this show...

676
00:45:23,850 --> 00:45:27,790
is clearing a misunderstanding we had.

677
00:45:28,690 --> 00:45:30,329
I said what I wanted to say...

678
00:45:30,330 --> 00:45:31,960
and remembered what I wanted to remember.

679
00:45:34,030 --> 00:45:35,330
Is there more you want to say?

680
00:45:36,930 --> 00:45:38,270
Did you remember what you wanted to remember?

681
00:45:39,500 --> 00:45:40,599
Yes, I did.

682
00:45:40,600 --> 00:45:42,810
I said, "I want to thank you," with those memories.

683
00:45:44,740 --> 00:45:45,780
I'm rooting for you.

684
00:45:48,140 --> 00:45:49,680
- Let's go.
- Thank you.

685
00:45:52,450 --> 00:45:57,090
(Yun Nyeong and Jae Hyeong's time finally stopped.)

686
00:45:57,290 --> 00:46:00,459
They met again six years after an immature relationship.

687
00:46:00,460 --> 00:46:03,559
- Their date had that vibe.
- Yes.

688
00:46:03,560 --> 00:46:04,889
They wrapped things up well.

689
00:46:04,890 --> 00:46:07,929
I don't know if there's such thing as a good breakup.

690
00:46:07,930 --> 00:46:09,629
- Right?
- But Yun Nyeong and Jae Hyeong...

691
00:46:09,630 --> 00:46:12,239
showed a textbook example...

692
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:13,240
- of a good breakup.
- I know.

693
00:46:13,241 --> 00:46:14,569
- Seriously.
- It was a good goodbye.

694
00:46:14,570 --> 00:46:15,969
After a breakup,

695
00:46:15,970 --> 00:46:18,009
people usually become less than strangers.

696
00:46:18,010 --> 00:46:19,039
- That's right.
- In a sense,

697
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:21,079
they showed that there's another way.

698
00:46:21,080 --> 00:46:23,309
The fact that they cleared up a misunderstanding...

699
00:46:23,310 --> 00:46:25,580
- makes this worthwhile for them.
- That's right.

700
00:46:26,650 --> 00:46:27,720
Did you sleep well?

701
00:46:27,950 --> 00:46:30,719
I didn't get much sleep. I got three hours of sleep.

702
00:46:30,720 --> 00:46:31,889
- Three hours of sleep?
- Yes.

703
00:46:31,890 --> 00:46:33,860
You didn't get much sleep. I got two hours of sleep.

704
00:46:34,160 --> 00:46:35,320
Why didn't you sleep more?

705
00:46:37,260 --> 00:46:40,230
(Hyeon Ji and Baek Hyun's date with ex)

706
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:42,370
Why did you only get two hours of sleep?

707
00:46:42,730 --> 00:46:43,870
- Me?
- Yes.

708
00:46:44,100 --> 00:46:45,640
I couldn't sleep.

709
00:46:46,300 --> 00:46:47,370
Why not?

710
00:46:51,570 --> 00:46:52,880
I just couldn't.

711
00:46:53,610 --> 00:46:54,940
Were you too excited?

712
00:46:55,010 --> 00:46:57,410
- Me? Was I too excited?
- Yes.

713
00:46:58,080 --> 00:46:59,220
Were you excited yesterday?

714
00:47:03,090 --> 00:47:04,190
Tell me.

715
00:47:05,090 --> 00:47:06,160
Were you excited?

716
00:47:11,690 --> 00:47:14,760
You rode Yoo Sik's car all along.

717
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:17,470
How does it feel to ride my car?

718
00:47:21,540 --> 00:47:24,210
- I know. I can't believe...
- How does it feel?

719
00:47:25,140 --> 00:47:27,280
You're driving in Japan.

720
00:47:27,610 --> 00:47:28,640
What?

721
00:47:29,450 --> 00:47:31,410
I can't believe you're driving.

722
00:47:32,650 --> 00:47:34,320
It felt so strange.

723
00:47:34,850 --> 00:47:39,090
When we dated, Baek Hyun couldn't drive.

724
00:47:39,720 --> 00:47:42,959
I couldn't believe it.

725
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:45,960
Seeing him drive...

726
00:47:46,930 --> 00:47:50,429
made me think, "So many years passed."

727
00:47:50,430 --> 00:47:52,740
It felt so strange.

728
00:47:54,340 --> 00:47:56,870
I couldn't walk. I couldn't travel anywhere...

729
00:47:56,910 --> 00:47:58,870
let alone drive.

730
00:47:59,040 --> 00:48:00,180
We couldn't...

731
00:48:01,480 --> 00:48:03,549
do the things...

732
00:48:03,550 --> 00:48:05,210
other couples did easily.

733
00:48:06,050 --> 00:48:08,519
Doing the things...

734
00:48:08,520 --> 00:48:09,950
we couldn't do back then...

735
00:48:10,190 --> 00:48:13,190
made me thankful and apologetic.

736
00:48:15,020 --> 00:48:16,560
I felt so sad.

737
00:48:23,030 --> 00:48:24,870
It has been a while since we went on a date.

738
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:30,010
Do you feel uncomfortable?

739
00:48:31,040 --> 00:48:32,040
No.

740
00:48:37,350 --> 00:48:39,850
You gave Yun Nyeong your bracelet.

741
00:48:40,620 --> 00:48:42,320
- My bracelet?
- Yes.

742
00:48:47,190 --> 00:48:49,160
You wore matching rings with Yoo Sik.

743
00:48:51,160 --> 00:48:52,289
I didn't wear it today.

744
00:48:52,290 --> 00:48:54,030
- Didn't you wear it today?
- No.

745
00:49:09,580 --> 00:49:11,409
Is this the sound of a creek?

746
00:49:11,410 --> 00:49:14,350
- Yes, there must be a creek.
- This place is so pretty.

747
00:49:15,180 --> 00:49:16,190
Right?

748
00:49:16,390 --> 00:49:19,420
It's the prettiest place I've visited here.

749
00:49:20,090 --> 00:49:22,159
There are so many hydrangeas.

750
00:49:22,160 --> 00:49:23,889
(The garden is full of hydrangeas, the flower Hyeon Ji likes)

751
00:49:23,890 --> 00:49:25,160
It's so pretty.

752
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:28,560
Do you know which colour of hydrangea I like the most?

753
00:49:29,970 --> 00:49:31,670
- The blue one.
- Yes.

754
00:49:32,100 --> 00:49:33,270
I suddenly remembered.

755
00:49:35,770 --> 00:49:36,870
I'll take photos.

756
00:49:44,510 --> 00:49:46,219
How does they look with the maple leaves?

757
00:49:46,220 --> 00:49:48,420
- They look good.
- Do they look good?

758
00:49:49,250 --> 00:49:50,720
I think I take better photos.

759
00:49:51,090 --> 00:49:52,120
No way.

760
00:49:52,320 --> 00:49:53,820
You're bad at taking photos.

761
00:49:54,520 --> 00:49:55,520
Did you take it?

762
00:49:58,530 --> 00:49:59,530
Stop it.

763
00:50:00,600 --> 00:50:01,600
Stop it.

764
00:50:04,830 --> 00:50:05,900
What's this?

765
00:50:08,470 --> 00:50:10,810
- You took nice photos.
- Right?

766
00:50:11,340 --> 00:50:12,840
- I took nice photos, right?
- Yes.

767
00:50:13,410 --> 00:50:14,480
Thank you.

768
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:18,610
- It's so nice.
- Yes.

769
00:50:20,080 --> 00:50:21,180
It feels strange.

770
00:50:22,520 --> 00:50:23,920
It's the last date.

771
00:50:27,260 --> 00:50:29,530
I didn't know that we'd go on a date at the very end.

772
00:50:31,360 --> 00:50:35,100
I can't think of anything to say because we don't have much time.

773
00:50:36,500 --> 00:50:37,800
Was there something you wanted to say?

774
00:50:39,900 --> 00:50:41,170
Did you think of what to say in advance?

775
00:50:47,040 --> 00:50:49,080
I'm sorry that I was so harsh to you here.

776
00:50:53,150 --> 00:50:54,350
I hurt your feelings.

777
00:50:55,990 --> 00:50:58,190
- It's okay.
- It isn't okay.

778
00:51:00,360 --> 00:51:02,190
Look at this. It's due to dislocation.

779
00:51:02,490 --> 00:51:03,530
What?

780
00:51:04,260 --> 00:51:06,700
- Did the bone get stuck...
- Yes.

781
00:51:06,930 --> 00:51:09,699
Like this? Did it harden like this?

782
00:51:09,700 --> 00:51:13,140
Yes. Apparently, tissues pile up and harden this way.

783
00:51:13,770 --> 00:51:16,210
Were your hands so small?

784
00:51:20,280 --> 00:51:21,280
Seriously.

785
00:51:23,380 --> 00:51:25,050
It feels strange to hold your hands after a long while.

786
00:51:26,680 --> 00:51:29,690
My hands? Why do you fall in love so easily?

787
00:51:30,320 --> 00:51:31,350
Me?

788
00:51:32,050 --> 00:51:33,759
- You fall in love easily.
- Why?

789
00:51:33,760 --> 00:51:34,790
Upon coming here...

790
00:51:35,320 --> 00:51:36,959
I fell in love with you easily.

791
00:51:36,960 --> 00:51:38,690
It happened so quickly.

792
00:51:39,900 --> 00:51:41,060
But you rejected me.

793
00:51:42,460 --> 00:51:44,170
I'll win you over no matter what.

794
00:51:45,400 --> 00:51:46,969
I thought you only did that with me.

795
00:51:46,970 --> 00:51:49,410
- What?
- I thought I was special.

796
00:51:53,080 --> 00:51:55,910
Watching you act like that made me unhappy.

797
00:51:56,850 --> 00:51:58,080
Had I asked you...

798
00:51:59,050 --> 00:52:00,849
to talk...

799
00:52:00,850 --> 00:52:03,750
and made my interest clear from the beginning,

800
00:52:08,090 --> 00:52:10,560
would you have expressed your feelings?

801
00:52:12,830 --> 00:52:16,000
I think I've expressed my feelings to you a lot.

802
00:52:17,530 --> 00:52:19,500
- Really?
- Do you disagree?

803
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:24,169
Was it Yoo Sik who asked me yesterday...

804
00:52:24,170 --> 00:52:26,240
- if I would've been swayed?
- Yes.

805
00:52:27,640 --> 00:52:30,549
I would've been swayed. But I knew...

806
00:52:30,550 --> 00:52:35,420
that getting back together with someone required a talk.

807
00:52:36,620 --> 00:52:41,420
But you were closed off...

808
00:52:42,320 --> 00:52:43,730
in my opinion.

809
00:52:45,360 --> 00:52:49,030
I want you to be happy.

810
00:52:51,130 --> 00:52:54,440
It's strange. A corner of my heart feels strange.

811
00:52:56,240 --> 00:53:00,010
She said that she would've been swayed...

812
00:53:02,080 --> 00:53:03,810
had we talked from the start.

813
00:53:06,650 --> 00:53:09,050
From the moment I learned about Hyeon Ji's feelings,

814
00:53:13,890 --> 00:53:15,820
I've felt strange.

815
00:53:22,700 --> 00:53:24,200
We need to eat.

816
00:53:24,670 --> 00:53:26,799
Yes. I'm pretty hungry now.

817
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:27,800
Are you hungry?

818
00:53:28,840 --> 00:53:30,070
Let's eat something tasty.

819
00:53:30,910 --> 00:53:32,810
You said that I ate a lot.

820
00:53:33,110 --> 00:53:34,810
- You do eat a lot.
- Yes.

821
00:53:35,310 --> 00:53:36,979
I eat a lot.

822
00:53:36,980 --> 00:53:38,079
Can't you eat as much here?

823
00:53:38,080 --> 00:53:39,979
Here, I feel like my stomach...

824
00:53:39,980 --> 00:53:41,780
What's this? You dropped it.

825
00:53:43,090 --> 00:53:44,150
It's an envelope with money.

826
00:53:44,790 --> 00:53:46,459
I brought Japanese yen as well.

827
00:53:46,460 --> 00:53:47,820
- Really?
- Yes.

828
00:53:49,430 --> 00:53:52,460
Still, it's so fascinating that we can converse with ease.

829
00:53:52,800 --> 00:53:55,500
If we still can't do that, it'll be a disaster.

830
00:53:55,730 --> 00:53:57,370
I guess time heals everything.

831
00:54:00,740 --> 00:54:03,710
It has been five years since we broke up.

832
00:54:03,940 --> 00:54:06,709
Would it be possible to cry after five years?

833
00:54:06,710 --> 00:54:07,710
Seriously.

834
00:54:12,450 --> 00:54:14,380
Yoo Sik put this in here yesterday.

835
00:54:14,920 --> 00:54:16,650
He can't find a four-leaf clover.

836
00:54:16,920 --> 00:54:18,819
He said that he preferred a three-leaf clover.

837
00:54:18,820 --> 00:54:20,889
He says that since it's hard to find a four-leaf clover.

838
00:54:20,890 --> 00:54:23,559
Three-leaf clovers are all over the place.

839
00:54:23,560 --> 00:54:25,860
- Apparently, the meaning is nicer.
- Happiness?

840
00:54:26,600 --> 00:54:28,300
Luck is better.

841
00:54:33,300 --> 00:54:35,240
The final decision is tomorrow.

842
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:36,610
Yes.

843
00:54:38,870 --> 00:54:40,080
Switch to me.

844
00:54:42,440 --> 00:54:44,249
- Do it.
- Do you want me to do that?

845
00:54:44,250 --> 00:54:45,950
Yes. Switch to me.

846
00:54:47,650 --> 00:54:48,720
Switch to me.

847
00:54:50,420 --> 00:54:51,490
My goodness.

848
00:54:54,760 --> 00:54:57,760
Three hours are bigger than eighteen days.

849
00:55:03,830 --> 00:55:06,839
- What? What's going on?
- Why is he saying that?

850
00:55:06,840 --> 00:55:08,639
"Three hours are bigger than eighteen days."

851
00:55:08,640 --> 00:55:10,269
Will she switch because of those three hours?

852
00:55:10,270 --> 00:55:11,809
I knew that this would happen.

853
00:55:11,810 --> 00:55:13,809
Why is he asking her...

854
00:55:13,810 --> 00:55:16,279
to switch to him at the very end?

855
00:55:16,280 --> 00:55:18,509
I think he's half joking and half serious.

856
00:55:18,510 --> 00:55:21,979
I feel like he hasn't gotten over the past memories...

857
00:55:21,980 --> 00:55:23,750
even after five years.

858
00:55:24,890 --> 00:55:28,590
It's my first time seeing the sea in such clear weather.

859
00:55:29,220 --> 00:55:31,530
It's so pretty, Hyeon Ji.

860
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:38,299
The weather must have lit up...

861
00:55:38,300 --> 00:55:40,000
- Gosh.
- because it's our last day.

862
00:55:41,940 --> 00:55:43,010
Goodness.

863
00:55:43,670 --> 00:55:44,910
What nice weather.

864
00:55:50,010 --> 00:55:51,180
It's like Gangneung.

865
00:55:52,180 --> 00:55:53,220
- The beach.
- Totally.

866
00:55:54,720 --> 00:55:56,620
- It does give off Gangneung vibes.
- Right?

867
00:55:59,890 --> 00:56:01,390
I had fun in Gangneung.

868
00:56:03,990 --> 00:56:06,430
When I could walk again after some rehabilitation,

869
00:56:06,760 --> 00:56:10,770
our first trip was to Gangneung.

870
00:56:11,330 --> 00:56:13,600
I have great memories of Gangneung.

871
00:56:14,040 --> 00:56:15,440
We didn't fight...

872
00:56:16,270 --> 00:56:17,840
and spent happy moments together.

873
00:56:17,940 --> 00:56:19,840
That's why it feels all the more special to me.

874
00:56:26,650 --> 00:56:28,580
Yesterday, out of the blue,

875
00:56:29,280 --> 00:56:30,420
you mentioned curry,

876
00:56:32,250 --> 00:56:35,090
but in a really cool way.

877
00:56:38,190 --> 00:56:39,700
I thought you'd know after tasting it.

878
00:56:44,700 --> 00:56:46,340
Really, the curry was amazing.

879
00:56:49,300 --> 00:56:50,639
Why didn't you have more?

880
00:56:50,640 --> 00:56:52,270
You won't be able to eat my food again.

881
00:57:01,550 --> 00:57:03,150
There's a way you can eat my food.

882
00:57:05,420 --> 00:57:06,659
- How?
- What?

883
00:57:06,660 --> 00:57:07,690
How?

884
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:09,019
I told you earlier.

885
00:57:09,020 --> 00:57:11,190
(To change your mind.)

886
00:57:17,970 --> 00:57:19,000
Are you done?

887
00:57:22,270 --> 00:57:23,640
Actually, I wrote a letter.

888
00:57:24,940 --> 00:57:26,040
I knew it.

889
00:57:26,540 --> 00:57:28,180
I didn't think you'd know.

890
00:57:29,750 --> 00:57:31,480
I know you well, you know?

891
00:57:35,880 --> 00:57:37,420
Seriously.

892
00:57:38,950 --> 00:57:39,960
Shall I read it for you?

893
00:57:41,590 --> 00:57:42,759
I'll read it.

894
00:57:42,760 --> 00:57:43,790
You will?

895
00:57:44,690 --> 00:57:45,830
Should I read it later?

896
00:57:46,230 --> 00:57:47,300
Read it now.

897
00:57:48,330 --> 00:57:49,559
Won't I get an upset stomach?

898
00:57:49,560 --> 00:57:50,670
Should I read it for you?

899
00:57:59,410 --> 00:58:01,309
(Hyeon Ji, it's been a while since I last wrote you a letter.)

900
00:58:01,310 --> 00:58:04,579
(As I wrote so many letters to you, )

901
00:58:04,580 --> 00:58:07,379
(I rarely wrote any after breaking up with you.)

902
00:58:07,380 --> 00:58:10,790
(Remember what you told me?)

903
00:58:10,920 --> 00:58:12,789
("You're very special to me, Baek Hyun.")

904
00:58:12,790 --> 00:58:14,659
(I hated you, got annoyed by you, and couldn't understand you.)

905
00:58:14,660 --> 00:58:16,429
(But I realised you and I were on the same page.)

906
00:58:16,430 --> 00:58:17,430
("Hyeon Ji, you were always a joy to me.")

907
00:58:17,430 --> 00:58:18,430
("I hope you become happy.")

908
00:58:18,431 --> 00:58:20,129
(I regret nothing.)

909
00:58:20,130 --> 00:58:22,399
(Even if we go back in time, )

910
00:58:22,400 --> 00:58:24,729
(regardless of how many times, )

911
00:58:24,730 --> 00:58:26,939
(I'd always...)

912
00:58:26,940 --> 00:58:30,970
(date you.)

913
00:58:36,980 --> 00:58:40,319
(We're now in our late 20s...)

914
00:58:40,320 --> 00:58:43,819
(and have become very mature, )

915
00:58:43,820 --> 00:58:46,519
(which is a relief.)

916
00:58:46,520 --> 00:58:48,419
("Hyeon Ji,")

917
00:58:48,420 --> 00:58:50,160
("you're also very special to me.")

918
00:58:50,190 --> 00:58:53,199
(Hyeon Ji, for making me...)

919
00:58:53,200 --> 00:58:58,030
(love you with all I had...)

920
00:58:58,070 --> 00:59:01,340
(Please be happy. Bye! June, 2025)

921
00:59:13,850 --> 00:59:16,820
I couldn't take my eyes off that last sentence.

922
00:59:17,150 --> 00:59:18,649
(From Baek Hyun, who loved you more than anyone else)

923
00:59:18,650 --> 00:59:22,420
"From Baek Hyun, who loved you more than anyone else."

924
00:59:24,590 --> 00:59:26,090
That made me...

925
00:59:26,960 --> 00:59:28,000
feel strange.

926
00:59:29,060 --> 00:59:30,600
It was in the past tense.

927
00:59:32,800 --> 00:59:36,300
The sentence held our time together.

928
00:59:36,640 --> 00:59:38,840
It held the time when Baek Hyun...

929
00:59:39,270 --> 00:59:41,679
joined the army and wrote letters to me...

930
00:59:41,680 --> 00:59:43,350
every single day.

931
00:59:44,150 --> 00:59:48,150
I was hit with the fact that this was our last moment together.

932
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:50,850
It made me sad.

933
01:00:00,230 --> 01:00:01,660
We don't have much time left.

934
01:00:32,330 --> 01:00:33,400
Don't cry.

935
01:00:37,830 --> 01:00:38,900
Don't cry.

936
01:00:41,440 --> 01:00:42,900
You have to go see Seung Yong.

937
01:00:53,050 --> 01:00:54,050
Come here.

938
01:00:57,320 --> 01:00:58,690
You'll ruin your makeup.

939
01:01:02,790 --> 01:01:04,130
Your handkerchief.

940
01:01:06,730 --> 01:01:08,830
(The handkerchief Baek Hyun left with Hyeon Ji)

941
01:01:09,460 --> 01:01:10,669
Can I use it?

942
01:01:10,670 --> 01:01:12,270
Yun Nyeong bought it for me.

943
01:01:13,740 --> 01:01:15,700
You're annoying.

944
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:20,080
I'm sorry, Yun Nyeong.

945
01:01:21,740 --> 01:01:22,910
To bring that of all things.

946
01:01:24,410 --> 01:01:25,450
Exactly.

947
01:01:30,550 --> 01:01:31,990
Seeing you laugh is nice.

948
01:01:33,660 --> 01:01:35,960
Don't cry. Don't cry because of me.

949
01:01:37,360 --> 01:01:38,360
Baek Hyun.

950
01:01:42,000 --> 01:01:43,100
Don't cry.

951
01:01:44,100 --> 01:01:46,699
I struggled hard not to cry,

952
01:01:46,700 --> 01:01:48,340
but Hyeon Ji cried buckets.

953
01:01:51,670 --> 01:01:52,910
I wanted to give her a hug...

954
01:01:53,710 --> 01:01:54,940
and comfort her.

955
01:01:58,880 --> 01:02:00,420
But I held back hard.

956
01:02:11,330 --> 01:02:12,990
I'm losing it.

957
01:02:16,030 --> 01:02:18,400
At least it's nice being with you.

958
01:02:26,240 --> 01:02:27,510
I got a text.

959
01:02:29,280 --> 01:02:31,079
(The date with your ex, Sung Baek Hyun, has ended.)

960
01:02:31,080 --> 01:02:33,150
(Please go to your next ex date.)

961
01:02:36,920 --> 01:02:38,490
Do you have to leave?

962
01:02:38,850 --> 01:02:39,890
Yes.

963
01:02:46,160 --> 01:02:47,260
It was fun.

964
01:02:48,730 --> 01:02:49,900
Although it was short,

965
01:02:50,730 --> 01:02:51,800
it couldn't be helped.

966
01:02:52,770 --> 01:02:55,000
- Seriously.
- Goodness.

967
01:02:56,240 --> 01:02:58,470
- Oh, well.
- It was too short.

968
01:03:12,220 --> 01:03:14,890
Must I leave? I'm the one who has to leave, right?

969
01:03:17,390 --> 01:03:18,460
Go ahead.

970
01:03:20,030 --> 01:03:21,300
How does it feel to leave me behind?

971
01:03:23,000 --> 01:03:24,070
You should leave.

972
01:03:25,700 --> 01:03:27,600
It's better for me to stay.

973
01:03:29,800 --> 01:03:30,810
Bye.

974
01:03:34,740 --> 01:03:35,840
Bye, Hyeon Ji.

975
01:03:46,960 --> 01:03:48,660
It was a bummer. A real bummer.

976
01:03:49,490 --> 01:03:53,660
There's always a sense of regret with Hyeon Ji.

977
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:56,599
Despite trying really hard to make decisions...

978
01:03:56,600 --> 01:03:58,170
and behave in ways I won't regret,

979
01:04:00,170 --> 01:04:02,440
it's tough when it comes to Hyeon Ji.

980
01:04:03,070 --> 01:04:05,940
Both after joining the show and when we were dating.

981
01:04:07,980 --> 01:04:10,780
I'm filled with sadness and regret.

982
01:04:12,510 --> 01:04:14,350
That moment was the worst.

983
01:04:18,120 --> 01:04:19,490
For goodness' sake.

984
01:04:22,720 --> 01:04:23,760
Gosh.

985
01:05:00,660 --> 01:05:01,700
Are you crying?

986
01:05:05,530 --> 01:05:06,570
What is it?

987
01:05:06,900 --> 01:05:07,940
I have to go.

988
01:05:08,700 --> 01:05:09,900
I have to.

989
01:05:11,510 --> 01:05:12,910
But you know...

990
01:05:13,380 --> 01:05:15,910
You always hugged me when I cried.

991
01:05:19,750 --> 01:05:20,950
Why are you crying?

992
01:05:31,190 --> 01:05:32,690
Oh, dear.

993
01:06:36,790 --> 01:06:38,360
Just...

994
01:06:47,540 --> 01:06:48,600
Go already.

995
01:06:49,600 --> 01:06:50,670
Really.

996
01:06:52,140 --> 01:06:54,580
This is the worst, Hyeon Ji.

997
01:06:57,480 --> 01:07:00,220
Seriously, if you cry,

998
01:07:00,820 --> 01:07:01,850
I...

999
01:07:03,950 --> 01:07:05,050
Get going.

1000
01:07:06,150 --> 01:07:07,720
Go.

1001
01:07:12,230 --> 01:07:13,260
Go.

1002
01:07:14,360 --> 01:07:15,360
Don't cry.

1003
01:07:15,660 --> 01:07:16,730
Okay. Go.

1004
01:07:17,930 --> 01:07:19,000
I'm sorry.

1005
01:07:22,100 --> 01:07:23,170
Go.

1006
01:07:29,580 --> 01:07:31,380
I really hate myself right now.

1007
01:07:35,220 --> 01:07:36,320
Come on. Go.

1008
01:07:39,820 --> 01:07:40,820
Go now.

1009
01:07:43,830 --> 01:07:44,860
Bye.

1010
01:07:45,830 --> 01:07:48,160
- I'm leaving.
- Okay, don't come back.

1011
01:07:49,860 --> 01:07:51,270
- You must leave.
- I will.

1012
01:07:51,870 --> 01:07:53,430
Pretend I never cried.

1013
01:07:54,270 --> 01:07:56,099
I hate it, okay?

1014
01:07:56,100 --> 01:07:57,670
Don't say anything weird.

1015
01:08:09,650 --> 01:08:10,920
Do you want me to go with you?

1016
01:08:11,890 --> 01:08:12,890
Go.

1017
01:08:22,730 --> 01:08:26,400
At that moment, strangely enough, I didn't want to let her go.

1018
01:08:27,170 --> 01:08:29,700
I didn't want her to leave.

1019
01:08:31,470 --> 01:08:34,940
Like I hugged Hyeon Ji whenever she cried...

1020
01:08:35,680 --> 01:08:37,310
and comforted her,

1021
01:08:37,850 --> 01:08:39,880
she did the same to me.

1022
01:08:41,220 --> 01:08:44,090
The feelings I kept bottling up...

1023
01:08:44,250 --> 01:08:47,559
burst all at once, and I couldn't stop it.

1024
01:08:47,560 --> 01:08:49,260
(Overwhelmed with uncontrollable emotions)

1025
01:08:50,190 --> 01:08:51,760
Honestly, I didn't want to let her go.

1026
01:08:59,770 --> 01:09:00,800
Goodness.

1027
01:09:02,470 --> 01:09:07,710
(Hyeon Ji and Baek Hyun's date with ex has ended.)

1028
01:09:08,040 --> 01:09:10,450
- I feel bad for Baek Hyun.
- I see.

1029
01:09:10,580 --> 01:09:12,449
Doesn't everyone have someone like them?

1030
01:09:12,450 --> 01:09:15,949
One that's deep in your heart, no matter how much time has passed.

1031
01:09:15,950 --> 01:09:17,389
- Of course.
- Right?

1032
01:09:17,390 --> 01:09:19,189
You have this ex you can't break free...

1033
01:09:19,190 --> 01:09:20,989
from from the time you dated them.

1034
01:09:20,990 --> 01:09:22,790
They are one of those memorable exes.

1035
01:09:22,920 --> 01:09:24,489
Five years ago was so intense for the two,

1036
01:09:24,490 --> 01:09:26,030
as if it had happened yesterday,

1037
01:09:26,130 --> 01:09:29,029
and they still can't overcome them.

1038
01:09:29,030 --> 01:09:31,000
Watching these two...

1039
01:09:31,170 --> 01:09:32,599
makes me feel like...

1040
01:09:32,600 --> 01:09:34,039
- they were once...
- Right.

1041
01:09:34,040 --> 01:09:35,770
The love of their lives.

1042
01:09:35,900 --> 01:09:37,969
I wonder how that feels.

1043
01:09:37,970 --> 01:09:40,679
Rather than getting back together,

1044
01:09:40,680 --> 01:09:42,939
that personally felt like a proper breakup.

1045
01:09:42,940 --> 01:09:44,509
- It's not a reunion.
- Right?

1046
01:09:44,510 --> 01:09:46,910
It's heartbreaking to see Baek Hyun cry.

1047
01:09:47,220 --> 01:09:49,619
He cried like a child.

1048
01:09:49,620 --> 01:09:50,620
Exactly.

1049
01:09:50,790 --> 01:09:52,250
Watching him hurts.

1050
01:10:08,300 --> 01:10:09,699
Isn't it really pretty here?

1051
01:10:09,700 --> 01:10:12,070
Yes, it's pretty. What's more, there's no one here.

1052
01:10:12,510 --> 01:10:13,680
I love it.

1053
01:10:16,410 --> 01:10:19,079
(Ji Hyeon and Won Kyu's date with ex)

1054
01:10:19,080 --> 01:10:20,280
It's not cold either.

1055
01:10:23,150 --> 01:10:24,789
I'm finally on a date.

1056
01:10:24,790 --> 01:10:27,090
(I'm finally on a date with my ex.)

1057
01:10:27,590 --> 01:10:31,290
"What should I talk about?" was what I thought.

1058
01:10:31,960 --> 01:10:33,800
Things were complicated.

1059
01:10:34,600 --> 01:10:36,660
But if this were the last moment,

1060
01:10:38,230 --> 01:10:40,570
I didn't want it to be too serious.

1061
01:10:41,240 --> 01:10:44,810
Eat good food, talk about interesting things, laugh,

1062
01:10:45,740 --> 01:10:47,810
and spend a nice day together.

1063
01:10:47,980 --> 01:10:49,840
That was what crossed my mind.

1064
01:10:50,850 --> 01:10:52,980
- Did you like playing in water?
- Yes.

1065
01:10:53,250 --> 01:10:54,420
- Really?
- Yes.

1066
01:10:55,580 --> 01:10:56,779
- Come on.
- We couldn't hang out...

1067
01:10:56,780 --> 01:10:57,989
because of studying, right?

1068
01:10:57,990 --> 01:10:59,020
Correct.

1069
01:10:59,720 --> 01:11:01,190
I like playing in water.

1070
01:11:01,390 --> 01:11:02,589
Don't you?

1071
01:11:02,590 --> 01:11:03,990
I totally do.

1072
01:11:13,570 --> 01:11:15,870
To be frank, it felt new.

1073
01:11:16,740 --> 01:11:18,370
I took photos for the first time in a while.

1074
01:11:20,270 --> 01:11:21,739
My ex asked...

1075
01:11:21,740 --> 01:11:23,340
if I liked playing in water.

1076
01:11:23,980 --> 01:11:25,810
And I do like playing in water.

1077
01:11:26,310 --> 01:11:28,579
Now that I think about it, there are many things...

1078
01:11:28,580 --> 01:11:30,250
we didn't do together.

1079
01:11:30,850 --> 01:11:33,320
"Why didn't we go..."

1080
01:11:34,890 --> 01:11:36,060
"to the beach together?"

1081
01:11:37,390 --> 01:11:40,960
We could've totally made the trip if I had adjusted...

1082
01:11:41,460 --> 01:11:43,430
my schedule and such.

1083
01:11:46,830 --> 01:11:48,270
I don't think you'll like it.

1084
01:11:49,900 --> 01:11:51,440
Move. Keep moving.

1085
01:11:57,550 --> 01:11:59,549
Those are the regrets I have.

1086
01:11:59,550 --> 01:12:01,380
You look like a muscle man.

1087
01:12:02,520 --> 01:12:04,290
- Isn't this one nice?
- Yes.

1088
01:12:04,390 --> 01:12:05,820
- I'll take photos of you.
- No.

1089
01:12:07,960 --> 01:12:09,190
I'm okay.

1090
01:12:11,660 --> 01:12:13,030
- Are you hungry?
- Yes.

1091
01:12:13,760 --> 01:12:14,800
Let's go.

1092
01:12:21,070 --> 01:12:23,040
I heard it's a home-cooked food restaurant.

1093
01:12:23,500 --> 01:12:25,810
- Hamburg steak.
- Hamburg steak and salmon.

1094
01:12:26,040 --> 01:12:27,070
How pretty.

1095
01:12:30,310 --> 01:12:32,010
The weather isn't as hot as you expected, right?

1096
01:12:32,980 --> 01:12:34,020
No.

1097
01:12:42,960 --> 01:12:45,529
You can easily hear birds chirping in Japan, and it's nice, isn't it?

1098
01:12:45,530 --> 01:12:47,090
Yes, we can hear them at our house too.

1099
01:12:47,530 --> 01:12:48,730
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1100
01:12:58,140 --> 01:12:59,140
The sound of birds chirping...

1101
01:12:59,140 --> 01:13:00,140
- is nice.
- Totally.

1102
01:13:00,240 --> 01:13:01,880
It's very clear.

1103
01:13:01,910 --> 01:13:03,510
There's a railroad in front.

1104
01:13:03,680 --> 01:13:04,780
Exactly.

1105
01:13:12,090 --> 01:13:14,590
I've been wanting to come to a home-cooked food restaurant.

1106
01:13:15,720 --> 01:13:16,820
To think I'd come with you.

1107
01:13:18,730 --> 01:13:19,790
Right?

1108
01:13:26,900 --> 01:13:28,700
- It looks good.
- I agree.

1109
01:13:29,140 --> 01:13:30,670
- Nice.
- The meal looks hearty.

1110
01:13:31,840 --> 01:13:32,970
I'm going to take photos.

1111
01:13:34,610 --> 01:13:35,980
- Is it good?
- Yes.

1112
01:13:36,280 --> 01:13:37,379
What does it taste like?

1113
01:13:37,380 --> 01:13:39,379
I can clearly taste the banana.

1114
01:13:39,380 --> 01:13:40,620
- Really?
- Yes.

1115
01:13:41,650 --> 01:13:43,050
(Taking photos of Won Kyu in secret)

1116
01:13:44,150 --> 01:13:46,750
(Won Kyu takes photos of Ji Hyeon without hiding.)

1117
01:13:52,130 --> 01:13:53,459
- Can I try it?
- Yes.

1118
01:13:53,460 --> 01:13:55,560
Where are the... I found them.

1119
01:14:01,070 --> 01:14:02,340
It tastes so good.

1120
01:14:02,500 --> 01:14:03,570
It's mine.

1121
01:14:06,070 --> 01:14:07,070
Isn't it good?

1122
01:14:08,380 --> 01:14:10,980
Whenever we made an order, I always picked the good one.

1123
01:14:13,280 --> 01:14:15,019
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you.

1124
01:14:15,020 --> 01:14:17,620
Do you want some of this?

1125
01:14:18,890 --> 01:14:20,090
- Here you go.
- Okay.

1126
01:14:21,260 --> 01:14:22,290
I also want some of yours.

1127
01:14:34,340 --> 01:14:35,340
By the way,

1128
01:14:39,740 --> 01:14:42,410
were you interested in more than one person during your stay here?

1129
01:14:47,280 --> 01:14:50,050
Do you ask because you think I got along better with Ji Yeon?

1130
01:14:53,420 --> 01:14:55,190
That's what I believed.

1131
01:14:57,160 --> 01:15:00,190
In the beginning, I thought that you'd move on.

1132
01:15:01,530 --> 01:15:05,200
That's why when you asked me out on a date...

1133
01:15:06,500 --> 01:15:07,500
You must've been surprised.

1134
01:15:08,070 --> 01:15:10,300
I was surprised. I don't know what's on your mind.

1135
01:15:11,740 --> 01:15:12,910
You asked me out when I was sleeping.

1136
01:15:13,980 --> 01:15:18,780
There's a type of person that you'd like to be with.

1137
01:15:18,980 --> 01:15:21,550
- Yes.
- In the past,

1138
01:15:21,850 --> 01:15:24,690
I never thought deeply about it.

1139
01:15:25,620 --> 01:15:28,389
Being a gentleman and taking good care of you.

1140
01:15:28,390 --> 01:15:29,420
Those are some examples.

1141
01:15:29,920 --> 01:15:32,559
From looking at other guys...

1142
01:15:32,560 --> 01:15:35,600
who care about minute details...

1143
01:15:35,700 --> 01:15:37,099
- Aren't they so gentle?
- Yes,

1144
01:15:37,100 --> 01:15:38,530
I realised a few things.

1145
01:15:40,130 --> 01:15:42,000
I asked you yesterday...

1146
01:15:42,100 --> 01:15:45,510
what aspect of Yoo Sik made your heart flutter the most.

1147
01:15:48,210 --> 01:15:51,480
I asked because that's something I should learn.

1148
01:15:52,180 --> 01:15:55,020
When I see and hear such things,

1149
01:15:55,580 --> 01:15:56,580
they speak to me.

1150
01:15:57,350 --> 01:16:01,459
"That's why Ji Hyeon reacted that way then."

1151
01:16:01,460 --> 01:16:02,660
"It must've disappointed her."

1152
01:16:03,090 --> 01:16:04,460
Things like that...

1153
01:16:04,560 --> 01:16:05,589
Do you understand me now?

1154
01:16:05,590 --> 01:16:07,460
Yes, they spoke to me.

1155
01:16:08,830 --> 01:16:09,830
Things like that.

1156
01:16:10,800 --> 01:16:11,900
That's one thing that I realised.

1157
01:16:14,370 --> 01:16:17,040
We wouldn't get back together thinking that we'd break up again.

1158
01:16:18,070 --> 01:16:20,840
- I agree.
- When I consider that seriously...

1159
01:16:22,010 --> 01:16:23,580
If we get back together,

1160
01:16:29,220 --> 01:16:30,989
do you think you could marry me?

1161
01:16:30,990 --> 01:16:34,090
Yes, I considered that before bringing this up.

1162
01:16:36,790 --> 01:16:39,030
There are things that we've discussed.

1163
01:16:39,790 --> 01:16:40,900
That's true.

1164
01:16:44,230 --> 01:16:46,000
During our stay here,

1165
01:16:47,570 --> 01:16:49,169
when I come back from my schedule,

1166
01:16:49,170 --> 01:16:51,940
- there are people at the house.
- Yes.

1167
01:16:53,310 --> 01:16:54,840
A meal is prepared.

1168
01:16:57,450 --> 01:16:58,810
Why am I getting teary?

1169
01:16:59,950 --> 01:17:00,950
What's wrong?

1170
01:17:03,120 --> 01:17:05,390
I liked how lively it was.

1171
01:17:12,360 --> 01:17:14,160
I've lived alone for so long.

1172
01:17:15,960 --> 01:17:18,070
Right. Both of us have.

1173
01:17:22,140 --> 01:17:24,610
I wouldn't get married to avoid living alone.

1174
01:17:26,570 --> 01:17:27,879
- It was really nice.
- Yes.

1175
01:17:27,880 --> 01:17:29,040
If I had a family,

1176
01:17:30,110 --> 01:17:32,480
this is how coming back home would feel.

1177
01:17:32,580 --> 01:17:33,580
Yes.

1178
01:17:33,980 --> 01:17:36,220
Someone would make me curry without me realising it.

1179
01:17:37,180 --> 01:17:38,190
Right.

1180
01:17:41,460 --> 01:17:43,390
"Would we be good together?"

1181
01:17:43,860 --> 01:17:46,660
"If we got back together, would we be happy?"

1182
01:17:47,930 --> 01:17:49,500
"If we get back into a relationship,"

1183
01:17:50,660 --> 01:17:53,170
"would that be the best choice?"

1184
01:17:54,340 --> 01:17:56,740
That's the biggest question I have.

1185
01:18:00,040 --> 01:18:01,139
I heard what he had to say,

1186
01:18:01,140 --> 01:18:03,280
but things still seemed complicated.

1187
01:18:04,310 --> 01:18:05,350
I still had...

1188
01:18:08,250 --> 01:18:10,320
a lot of doubt.

1189
01:18:10,520 --> 01:18:12,690
We already broke up once.

1190
01:18:13,420 --> 01:18:15,360
Would we be happy if we get back together?

1191
01:18:16,990 --> 01:18:18,889
I wanted to take more time...

1192
01:18:18,890 --> 01:18:20,260
to understand what I really felt.

1193
01:18:21,630 --> 01:18:22,859
- Shall we go?
- Yes.

1194
01:18:22,860 --> 01:18:28,000
(They still have mixed feelings.)

1195
01:18:32,170 --> 01:18:33,209
Let's go.

1196
01:18:33,210 --> 01:18:38,180
(Ji Hyeon and Won Kyu's ex date has ended.)

1197
01:18:38,280 --> 01:18:40,079
Is it because every couple is wearing matching outfits?

1198
01:18:40,080 --> 01:18:41,080
Why do they look so good together?

1199
01:18:41,081 --> 01:18:42,749
We can't ignore their energy...

1200
01:18:42,750 --> 01:18:43,879
because they were together before.

1201
01:18:43,880 --> 01:18:45,819
- Right, I agree.
- They look so comfortable.

1202
01:18:45,820 --> 01:18:48,389
Their ex date seemed like...

1203
01:18:48,390 --> 01:18:51,959
a date to prepare for getting back together.

1204
01:18:51,960 --> 01:18:53,189
That's how I saw it.

1205
01:18:53,190 --> 01:18:55,459
- She asked him about marriage...
- Right.

1206
01:18:55,460 --> 01:18:56,829
- in case they got back together.
- Right.

1207
01:18:56,830 --> 01:18:57,899
- Her question clearly shows...
- Already.

1208
01:18:57,900 --> 01:18:59,599
That she's considering getting back...

1209
01:18:59,600 --> 01:19:00,600
- with him.
- Yes.

1210
01:19:00,600 --> 01:19:01,600
I agree.

1211
01:19:01,601 --> 01:19:04,069
For this couple,

1212
01:19:04,070 --> 01:19:06,569
one of them has to change drastically for the other person.

1213
01:19:06,570 --> 01:19:07,909
The effort must be consistent.

1214
01:19:07,910 --> 01:19:09,039
Then they wouldn't fight...

1215
01:19:09,040 --> 01:19:10,580
- in their relationship.
- Right.

1216
01:19:26,190 --> 01:19:29,630
I've been looking forward to my ex date the most.

1217
01:19:30,530 --> 01:19:32,499
My biggest hope was...

1218
01:19:32,500 --> 01:19:35,670
having a good time with her like we did in the past.

1219
01:19:37,840 --> 01:19:40,439
My heart fluttered a lot.

1220
01:19:40,440 --> 01:19:42,840
I hadn't been so nervous like this in a while.

1221
01:19:54,220 --> 01:19:56,389
My ex likes it when I style my hair...

1222
01:19:56,390 --> 01:19:57,560
and show my forehead.

1223
01:19:57,660 --> 01:20:00,330
I tried my best to look formal.

1224
01:20:17,140 --> 01:20:21,850
(Hyeon Ji and Seung Yong's date with ex)

1225
01:20:29,720 --> 01:20:31,530
Why do you look so upset?

1226
01:20:36,430 --> 01:20:37,559
- What's wrong?
- Was it hard to get here?

1227
01:20:37,560 --> 01:20:39,130
- What?
- Was it hard to get here?

1228
01:20:39,730 --> 01:20:41,039
- Getting here?
- Yes.

1229
01:20:41,040 --> 01:20:42,370
I took the escalator.

1230
01:20:43,370 --> 01:20:44,370
What about lunch?

1231
01:20:45,140 --> 01:20:47,440
- I had a light lunch.
- You did?

1232
01:20:47,910 --> 01:20:49,540
Your hair turned out well today.

1233
01:20:50,540 --> 01:20:52,909
I got ready early this morning.

1234
01:20:52,910 --> 01:20:53,910
At what time?

1235
01:20:53,911 --> 01:20:55,920
A little before 10am.

1236
01:20:56,650 --> 01:20:58,250
I even took a half body bath.

1237
01:20:59,490 --> 01:21:00,550
To get rid of swelling.

1238
01:21:03,890 --> 01:21:05,060
How do you feel physically?

1239
01:21:05,490 --> 01:21:07,030
Physically? I'm tired.

1240
01:21:07,360 --> 01:21:08,360
You're tired?

1241
01:21:09,760 --> 01:21:11,429
I thought that you'd wear something short today,

1242
01:21:11,430 --> 01:21:12,970
so I brought a blanket.

1243
01:21:13,070 --> 01:21:14,700
- Really?
- The blanket will be useless.

1244
01:21:16,270 --> 01:21:18,839
I've been wanting to wear this dress.

1245
01:21:18,840 --> 01:21:19,910
- I see.
- What do you think?

1246
01:21:20,010 --> 01:21:21,010
It's pretty.

1247
01:21:21,011 --> 01:21:22,809
It makes me look so mature...

1248
01:21:22,810 --> 01:21:24,179
that I couldn't put it on.

1249
01:21:24,180 --> 01:21:25,979
You don't look too mature. It looks good on you.

1250
01:21:25,980 --> 01:21:28,149
Since I'm on a date with the oldest person today,

1251
01:21:28,150 --> 01:21:29,680
I could put it on.

1252
01:21:31,220 --> 01:21:32,750
We're the oldest.

1253
01:21:32,950 --> 01:21:33,990
Exactly.

1254
01:21:35,890 --> 01:21:36,960
Does my hair look strange?

1255
01:21:37,160 --> 01:21:38,530
No, you styled it well.

1256
01:21:39,660 --> 01:21:40,690
It looks good right now.

1257
01:21:41,700 --> 01:21:43,760
Thank you. You look pretty today too.

1258
01:21:44,970 --> 01:21:46,199
You look very calm.

1259
01:21:46,200 --> 01:21:47,270
Really?

1260
01:21:47,570 --> 01:21:50,070
Did you take a look at the sea?

1261
01:21:50,670 --> 01:21:53,670
Yes, I was in front of the sea a moment ago.

1262
01:21:54,270 --> 01:21:56,639
- No, I mean up here.
- No.

1263
01:21:56,640 --> 01:21:58,850
When you go up, there's a beautiful view of the sea.

1264
01:21:59,180 --> 01:22:01,649
It feels like hiking without hiking.

1265
01:22:01,650 --> 01:22:02,680
I see.

1266
01:22:03,650 --> 01:22:05,220
It's interesting.

1267
01:22:07,690 --> 01:22:09,020
- What is it?
- Nothing.

1268
01:22:12,260 --> 01:22:14,599
She looked beautiful to me.

1269
01:22:14,600 --> 01:22:18,329
I really hoped to go on dates with her...

1270
01:22:18,330 --> 01:22:20,630
like we did in the past.

1271
01:22:24,510 --> 01:22:27,670
It felt like we were on our first date.

1272
01:22:27,740 --> 01:22:29,680
(A bracelet from Seung Yong)

1273
01:22:30,440 --> 01:22:32,610
It's unusual to see you wearing this bracelet.

1274
01:22:32,810 --> 01:22:33,979
- What?
- It's unusual...

1275
01:22:33,980 --> 01:22:35,550
It goes well with the outfit.

1276
01:22:41,890 --> 01:22:43,860
- Doesn't your ear hurt?
- No.

1277
01:22:44,560 --> 01:22:45,560
That's a relief.

1278
01:22:48,100 --> 01:22:50,060
I didn't expect a place like this here.

1279
01:22:50,360 --> 01:22:52,430
- Aren't you hungry?
- A little.

1280
01:22:59,070 --> 01:23:00,670
We finally go on a date.

1281
01:23:01,210 --> 01:23:02,210
I know.

1282
01:23:03,210 --> 01:23:04,979
It took a long time.

1283
01:23:04,980 --> 01:23:06,779
This is what Baek Hyun said earlier.

1284
01:23:06,780 --> 01:23:09,820
If I had to pick between you and him for the ex date,

1285
01:23:10,220 --> 01:23:11,850
he would've let me pick you.

1286
01:23:13,120 --> 01:23:14,790
So I told him, "You're the real deal."

1287
01:23:16,760 --> 01:23:18,860
"Baek Hyun, you're the real deal."

1288
01:23:20,630 --> 01:23:21,630
Seriously.

1289
01:23:28,870 --> 01:23:30,040
He's mature.

1290
01:23:30,570 --> 01:23:31,570
- You mean, Baek Hyun?
- Yes.

1291
01:23:31,571 --> 01:23:33,070
Everyone here is mature...

1292
01:23:33,740 --> 01:23:34,740
except me.

1293
01:23:35,110 --> 01:23:36,110
That's right.

1294
01:23:37,540 --> 01:23:39,910
- That's right.
- I'm just being honest.

1295
01:23:46,320 --> 01:23:48,090
The weather is nice now that we're sitting here.

1296
01:23:48,260 --> 01:23:49,660
Earlier, the sun was strong.

1297
01:23:50,460 --> 01:23:51,990
The view is really beautiful.

1298
01:23:52,430 --> 01:23:53,460
- I agree.
- It feels like Europe.

1299
01:23:57,800 --> 01:23:59,170
- Is it French toast?
- Will this be enough?

1300
01:23:59,270 --> 01:24:00,300
Yes, it will be fine.

1301
01:24:04,040 --> 01:24:05,040
Goodness.

1302
01:24:07,040 --> 01:24:09,410
I didn't drink a lot of coffee since I came here.

1303
01:24:09,510 --> 01:24:12,180
Really? How is that possible?

1304
01:24:13,080 --> 01:24:16,380
I didn't want my heart to beat too fast.

1305
01:24:16,480 --> 01:24:18,090
Did your heart flutter that much?

1306
01:24:19,790 --> 01:24:20,790
Goodness.

1307
01:24:20,791 --> 01:24:22,860
I felt very nervous.

1308
01:24:23,060 --> 01:24:24,219
I had a maximum...

1309
01:24:24,220 --> 01:24:25,730
of one cup a day.

1310
01:24:29,730 --> 01:24:32,730
Anyway, I've been waiting only for this day.

1311
01:24:36,570 --> 01:24:39,340
Just last year,

1312
01:24:41,210 --> 01:24:43,209
eating out and drinking coffee together was...

1313
01:24:43,210 --> 01:24:45,210
very normal.

1314
01:24:46,110 --> 01:24:48,180
After waiting 8 or 9 days,

1315
01:24:48,750 --> 01:24:50,080
we barely had a meal together.

1316
01:24:50,880 --> 01:24:54,420
Thinking that this could be our last time...

1317
01:24:55,120 --> 01:24:57,220
made me feel very sad.

1318
01:24:57,320 --> 01:24:59,989
So I was very depressed on my way here.

1319
01:24:59,990 --> 01:25:01,330
- On your way here?
- Yes.

1320
01:25:03,230 --> 01:25:04,970
When you think that it's the last time,

1321
01:25:06,270 --> 01:25:07,670
it can be upsetting.

1322
01:25:09,100 --> 01:25:11,910
To be honest, I don't regret it.

1323
01:25:13,570 --> 01:25:15,510
Whatever the reason may be,

1324
01:25:15,710 --> 01:25:17,880
throughout my whole life,

1325
01:25:18,280 --> 01:25:22,380
I had never been so honest with anyone.

1326
01:25:22,580 --> 01:25:26,549
After coming here, it was my first time letting go of my pride...

1327
01:25:26,550 --> 01:25:27,690
to talk to you.

1328
01:25:28,860 --> 01:25:32,490
I think that I did my best,

1329
01:25:33,060 --> 01:25:34,460
so...

1330
01:25:36,300 --> 01:25:37,659
Being here...

1331
01:25:37,660 --> 01:25:40,970
gave me a chance to try that.

1332
01:25:41,370 --> 01:25:43,399
I feel much lighter now.

1333
01:25:43,400 --> 01:25:45,610
I'm glad about that.

1334
01:25:48,710 --> 01:25:51,480
I was very surprised...

1335
01:25:52,280 --> 01:25:56,020
to see you let go of your pride.

1336
01:25:56,220 --> 01:25:57,990
I thought that it was impressive.

1337
01:26:04,520 --> 01:26:07,329
To an extent,

1338
01:26:07,330 --> 01:26:08,430
I agree with you.

1339
01:26:08,530 --> 01:26:10,160
- About the realistic issue?
- Yes.

1340
01:26:10,400 --> 01:26:11,430
Right.

1341
01:26:12,470 --> 01:26:13,730
I have a lot on my mind.

1342
01:26:14,430 --> 01:26:17,840
I've wanted to get married.

1343
01:26:19,970 --> 01:26:22,639
We don't have much time here.

1344
01:26:22,640 --> 01:26:25,450
It's hard to find out if the other person is...

1345
01:26:25,910 --> 01:26:28,280
ready to get married or not.

1346
01:26:28,780 --> 01:26:30,950
In this uncertain situation,

1347
01:26:32,050 --> 01:26:34,620
I made an effort to reassure you.

1348
01:26:35,520 --> 01:26:38,389
If I didn't think that I was able to get married,

1349
01:26:38,390 --> 01:26:40,490
I wouldn't have suggested getting back together.

1350
01:26:42,460 --> 01:26:43,900
I'm not a fool.

1351
01:26:48,970 --> 01:26:50,340
You're really...

1352
01:26:52,770 --> 01:26:53,770
What?

1353
01:26:56,440 --> 01:26:59,149
Actually, I felt very pessimistic...

1354
01:26:59,150 --> 01:27:00,380
when you told me...

1355
01:27:01,720 --> 01:27:04,150
your thoughts that you had prepared.

1356
01:27:04,920 --> 01:27:08,319
I thought that it was too late.

1357
01:27:08,320 --> 01:27:12,360
But after seeing all the efforts you were making,

1358
01:27:14,960 --> 01:27:16,430
I didn't feel good about it.

1359
01:27:20,030 --> 01:27:21,840
Don't worry about me.

1360
01:27:22,040 --> 01:27:24,270
Just follow your heart.

1361
01:27:24,870 --> 01:27:26,240
It's not so difficult.

1362
01:27:27,940 --> 01:27:30,080
But you make it difficult.

1363
01:27:32,210 --> 01:27:36,180
You keep giving me too much to think about.

1364
01:27:38,120 --> 01:27:39,620
Isn't it over today?

1365
01:27:41,490 --> 01:27:43,320
I'll probably see him tonight at home.

1366
01:27:43,860 --> 01:27:44,860
I'm not sure.

1367
01:27:50,030 --> 01:27:51,429
(The date with ex has ended.)

1368
01:27:51,430 --> 01:27:52,829
(Please text the name of one person, excluding your ex.)

1369
01:27:52,830 --> 01:27:54,270
(If you choose each other, you’ll get to go on a secret date.)

1370
01:27:55,670 --> 01:27:56,670
What is it?

1371
01:27:58,310 --> 01:27:59,640
Our date has ended.

1372
01:28:02,080 --> 01:28:03,080
Really?

1373
01:29:10,540 --> 01:29:11,580
Why are you crying?

1374
01:29:40,770 --> 01:29:41,840
Respond to the text.

1375
01:29:44,640 --> 01:29:45,680
Shall I send one instead?

1376
01:29:51,350 --> 01:29:53,420
Goodness.

1377
01:30:01,490 --> 01:30:03,030
I didn't want to cry.

1378
01:30:03,630 --> 01:30:05,299
Seung Yong, please don't cry.

1379
01:30:05,300 --> 01:30:07,130
You didn't cry when I cried.

1380
01:30:09,040 --> 01:30:12,540
I have to deal with...

1381
01:30:13,770 --> 01:30:15,280
my own pain.

1382
01:30:16,680 --> 01:30:18,310
Don't worry about that.

1383
01:30:19,980 --> 01:30:21,679
I hope that you'll decide...

1384
01:30:21,680 --> 01:30:23,480
what makes you happy.

1385
01:30:27,850 --> 01:30:30,790
I did my best so that I don't regret it.

1386
01:30:31,120 --> 01:30:32,490
You should do the same.

1387
01:30:34,460 --> 01:30:35,560
That sounds scary.

1388
01:30:36,760 --> 01:30:39,600
I'm satisfied with what I did.

1389
01:30:40,230 --> 01:30:41,770
I won't regret it.

1390
01:30:43,100 --> 01:30:44,910
If I can't make you...

1391
01:30:45,770 --> 01:30:47,409
come back to me,

1392
01:30:47,410 --> 01:30:49,980
I'll be ready to accept it.

1393
01:30:54,080 --> 01:30:55,980
Goodness.

1394
01:31:04,890 --> 01:31:06,160
Do you want to say anything else?

1395
01:31:14,500 --> 01:31:15,600
See you later.

1396
01:31:23,240 --> 01:31:24,310
Let's stay strong.

1397
01:31:25,980 --> 01:31:27,709
- Don't cry.
- What?

1398
01:31:27,710 --> 01:31:28,950
Don't cry.

1399
01:31:29,620 --> 01:31:30,650
Okay.

1400
01:31:38,430 --> 01:31:39,460
Seriously.

1401
01:31:44,360 --> 01:31:45,500
I'll get going.

1402
01:32:25,740 --> 01:32:27,170
There's a sense of regret.

1403
01:32:27,940 --> 01:32:30,610
My thoughts kept going in a negative direction.

1404
01:32:37,920 --> 01:32:40,420
It felt like I was going through the breakup again.

1405
01:32:47,590 --> 01:32:48,830
Oh, no. That's too bad.

1406
01:32:48,960 --> 01:32:51,399
He tried everything he could and put his heart into it.

1407
01:32:51,400 --> 01:32:53,899
As they were nearing the end, they finally went on a date.

1408
01:32:53,900 --> 01:32:55,299
But he must have felt nothing had changed.

1409
01:32:55,300 --> 01:32:56,869
- Right.
- Once that crossed his mind,

1410
01:32:56,870 --> 01:33:00,409
it almost seemed like he had given up...

1411
01:33:00,410 --> 01:33:03,279
- during their conversation.
- Yes.

1412
01:33:03,280 --> 01:33:05,209
But it's not like...

1413
01:33:05,210 --> 01:33:07,379
- he can control her feelings.
- Of course, not.

1414
01:33:07,380 --> 01:33:09,449
He actually said that it felt like he was going through...

1415
01:33:09,450 --> 01:33:11,020
- the breakup again.
- Right.

1416
01:33:13,690 --> 01:33:15,759
(Kamakura House)

1417
01:33:15,760 --> 01:33:16,790
Sit down.

1418
01:33:17,260 --> 01:33:20,460
(Baek Hyun and Woo Jin come back after the date with their ex.)

1419
01:33:21,330 --> 01:33:23,460
My gosh. It's just the two of us again.

1420
01:33:24,430 --> 01:33:25,900
There should be one more.

1421
01:33:26,500 --> 01:33:27,500
He must be in his room.

1422
01:33:28,440 --> 01:33:30,340
I don't know. It's over now.

1423
01:33:30,540 --> 01:33:33,410
The date with the ex was quite a big deal.

1424
01:33:34,170 --> 01:33:36,380
We went to a restaurant that overlooked the ocean.

1425
01:33:36,780 --> 01:33:39,310
When we were dating, I couldn't walk for six months.

1426
01:33:39,610 --> 01:33:42,150
So I went through physical therapy and waited until my leg healed.

1427
01:33:42,280 --> 01:33:44,180
We went to Gangneung on our first trip together.

1428
01:33:45,050 --> 01:33:49,060
She said the ocean reminded her of Gangneung.

1429
01:33:49,160 --> 01:33:50,890
- The ocean?
- Yes.

1430
01:33:53,130 --> 01:33:54,130
I see.

1431
01:33:56,630 --> 01:33:58,060
I ended up crying my eyes out.

1432
01:33:59,070 --> 01:34:00,399
That's what this show does to you...

1433
01:34:00,400 --> 01:34:01,730
even if you have no lingering feelings.

1434
01:34:03,170 --> 01:34:06,170
We used to be lovers in the past.

1435
01:34:08,780 --> 01:34:10,710
So there's nothing we can do about our tears.

1436
01:34:13,380 --> 01:34:15,550
- I won't be able to see her again.
- Exactly.

1437
01:34:17,520 --> 01:34:19,390
- Our meeting...
- I really can't see her again.

1438
01:34:20,090 --> 01:34:21,990
- Hyeon Ji?
- Yes.

1439
01:34:24,060 --> 01:34:25,530
This is heartbreaking.

1440
01:34:26,690 --> 01:34:29,460
I really didn't want to cry on the show.

1441
01:34:29,860 --> 01:34:31,130
How many times did you cry?

1442
01:34:31,430 --> 01:34:33,300
I cried more than I expected.

1443
01:34:33,670 --> 01:34:34,930
I cried five times if you count today.

1444
01:34:37,600 --> 01:34:38,640
Whatever. It's about the same.

1445
01:34:39,710 --> 01:34:41,610
My gosh. I can't stop crying.

1446
01:34:45,580 --> 01:34:46,750
How beautiful.

1447
01:34:47,750 --> 01:34:48,850
This place is nice.

1448
01:34:49,920 --> 01:34:51,990
This is my second romantic moment with you on the show.

1449
01:34:53,150 --> 01:34:54,720
The first moment was in Pyeongchang-dong.

1450
01:34:55,520 --> 01:34:56,920
We're having another moment here.

1451
01:34:59,260 --> 01:35:00,990
- Come here.
- Okay.

1452
01:35:02,330 --> 01:35:03,500
The view from this spot is much better.

1453
01:35:07,600 --> 01:35:10,299
I cried like crazy in my dream after I came back.

1454
01:35:10,300 --> 01:35:11,910
Is it because of your date with Hyeon Ji?

1455
01:35:12,210 --> 01:35:13,710
I cried because of Park Hyeon Ji.

1456
01:35:16,980 --> 01:35:18,440
I wonder what she means to me.

1457
01:35:21,610 --> 01:35:22,949
She's not your first love, right?

1458
01:35:22,950 --> 01:35:24,779
Actually, she is.

1459
01:35:24,780 --> 01:35:26,750
- She's your first love?
- Yes.

1460
01:35:28,220 --> 01:35:31,720
(An unforgettable feeling pierces through his heart.)

1461
01:35:33,330 --> 01:35:35,660
(Their day with their ex is coming to an end.)

1462
01:35:37,730 --> 01:35:40,430
(It's late, and darkness has set in.)

1463
01:35:41,700 --> 01:35:45,140
(Yoo Sik arrives at the secret date spot.)

1464
01:35:48,640 --> 01:35:53,280
(Hayama Torigin)

1465
01:35:59,450 --> 01:36:03,190
Actually, I wanted to talk to her about the game of truth or dare...

1466
01:36:03,460 --> 01:36:06,159
from the night before and where we stood...

1467
01:36:06,160 --> 01:36:07,730
in a more serious manner.

1468
01:36:08,060 --> 01:36:09,560
So I chose her for my the secret date.

1469
01:36:14,130 --> 01:36:15,769
- Right. They should talk.
- Yes.

1470
01:36:15,770 --> 01:36:17,769
- They must.
- They didn't have a heart-to-heart.

1471
01:36:17,770 --> 01:36:19,139
They must have it here. Seriously.

1472
01:36:19,140 --> 01:36:21,309
If they don't, she might change her mind.

1473
01:36:21,310 --> 01:36:22,380
Totally.

1474
01:36:23,940 --> 01:36:27,680
(And the seat next to him is still empty.)

1475
01:36:39,690 --> 01:36:41,290
I was only half certain.

1476
01:36:42,260 --> 01:36:44,900
I knew that she was still trying to make up her mind.

1477
01:36:45,830 --> 01:36:48,800
And she went on a date with her exes during the day.

1478
01:36:49,800 --> 01:36:54,010
I did think there was a possibility that she might not choose to see me.

1479
01:37:05,080 --> 01:37:09,320
(Time keeps drifting by without any certainty.)

1480
01:37:32,280 --> 01:37:33,280
(Hyeon Ji and Yoo Sik's secret date)

1481
01:37:33,281 --> 01:37:35,620
What took you so long?

1482
01:37:37,380 --> 01:37:38,420
Seriously.

1483
01:37:39,050 --> 01:37:41,050
You're always so busy.

1484
01:37:41,820 --> 01:37:43,460
I wanted to come sooner too.

1485
01:37:43,860 --> 01:37:45,360
- You did?
- Yes.

1486
01:38:02,580 --> 01:38:05,010
I did think there might come a time when our choices...

1487
01:38:05,850 --> 01:38:07,680
didn't align.

1488
01:38:08,680 --> 01:38:09,680
But I was wrong.

1489
01:38:10,620 --> 01:38:11,620
What do you mean?

1490
01:38:12,050 --> 01:38:13,290
Picking each other for dates?

1491
01:38:14,490 --> 01:38:15,490
Yes.

1492
01:38:19,390 --> 01:38:20,690
I thought it could happen.

1493
01:38:22,230 --> 01:38:24,260
I thought I might go home early tonight.

1494
01:38:26,500 --> 01:38:27,500
Oh, tonight?

1495
01:38:28,330 --> 01:38:29,800
- Yes.
- Because of a change of heart?

1496
01:38:30,140 --> 01:38:31,170
Who? Me?

1497
01:38:32,000 --> 01:38:33,239
It could have been either one of us.

1498
01:38:33,240 --> 01:38:34,540
- Either you or me.
- Right.

1499
01:38:35,780 --> 01:38:37,080
I thought you had a change of heart.

1500
01:38:38,410 --> 01:38:39,580
"Good job."

1501
01:38:40,610 --> 01:38:41,850
That's what I told myself.

1502
01:38:44,620 --> 01:38:46,120
Did the date go well?

1503
01:38:46,990 --> 01:38:48,050
What date?

1504
01:38:49,360 --> 01:38:50,489
- Today's date?
- Yes.

1505
01:38:50,490 --> 01:38:51,889
(She's curious about Yoo Sik's date with his ex.)

1506
01:38:51,890 --> 01:38:53,060
Did it go well?

1507
01:39:00,600 --> 01:39:02,200
It was a complicated date.

1508
01:39:06,940 --> 01:39:09,140
(Sighing)

1509
01:39:09,210 --> 01:39:10,680
- What?
- What?

1510
01:39:15,650 --> 01:39:19,290
I was slightly worried.

1511
01:39:19,790 --> 01:39:22,420
I thought that Yoo Sik's feelings...

1512
01:39:23,260 --> 01:39:27,060
might be swayed after the date with his ex.

1513
01:39:27,430 --> 01:39:29,730
Even I have a lot on my mind right now.

1514
01:39:30,400 --> 01:39:32,930
So the date might have confused him even more.

1515
01:39:33,970 --> 01:39:36,399
I was worried about that slightly more than anything.

1516
01:39:36,400 --> 01:39:37,400
(Unlike before, she's choosing her words carefully.)

1517
01:39:48,010 --> 01:39:49,180
- It's so good.
- Is it good?

1518
01:39:50,950 --> 01:39:53,020
- Dig in.
- Let's eat.

1519
01:39:58,760 --> 01:39:59,790
Is it good?

1520
01:40:10,140 --> 01:40:11,140
What is it?

1521
01:40:12,840 --> 01:40:14,410
I won't avoid your gaze now.

1522
01:40:21,910 --> 01:40:23,680
You never look away, seriously.

1523
01:40:29,320 --> 01:40:30,660
- What is it?
- What?

1524
01:40:33,060 --> 01:40:34,060
Are you full?

1525
01:40:34,360 --> 01:40:35,429
No.

1526
01:40:35,430 --> 01:40:36,600
- You're not full?
- No.

1527
01:40:39,070 --> 01:40:40,330
I'll be honest.

1528
01:40:44,170 --> 01:40:45,439
As you probably know,

1529
01:40:45,440 --> 01:40:48,140
I don't open up to people about my feelings.

1530
01:40:49,210 --> 01:40:52,040
I'm not criticizing people who do. I'm just saying...

1531
01:40:52,250 --> 01:40:54,680
that I don't make decisions about my feelings lightly.

1532
01:40:55,180 --> 01:40:56,880
That's why I really thought that...

1533
01:40:58,220 --> 01:40:59,650
I wouldn't be sure until the end.

1534
01:41:01,790 --> 01:41:02,860
But...

1535
01:41:05,260 --> 01:41:07,730
I really enjoyed every date with you.

1536
01:41:12,830 --> 01:41:14,270
I really liked spending time with you.

1537
01:41:16,000 --> 01:41:17,300
You didn't feel like an older woman.

1538
01:41:20,410 --> 01:41:22,510
If that's how you came across to me,

1539
01:41:23,580 --> 01:41:25,080
I wouldn't have felt...

1540
01:41:25,340 --> 01:41:28,050
the urge to take care of you. You know?

1541
01:41:28,180 --> 01:41:30,520
You thought you had to take care of me?

1542
01:41:31,380 --> 01:41:32,750
You don't think I did?

1543
01:41:36,420 --> 01:41:37,420
I did.

1544
01:41:39,430 --> 01:41:41,230
You always tried to take care of me.

1545
01:41:47,530 --> 01:41:50,270
I know I'm sharing this as we're approaching the end.

1546
01:41:51,800 --> 01:41:52,869
That's how I feel.

1547
01:41:52,870 --> 01:41:54,270
(That's how I feel about you.)

1548
01:41:57,580 --> 01:41:59,310
I was really grateful to you.

1549
01:42:02,180 --> 01:42:03,280
I mean it.

1550
01:42:15,030 --> 01:42:18,330
Didn't you say yesterday that you hadn't made up your mind yet?

1551
01:42:22,440 --> 01:42:23,670
You mean my final decision?

1552
01:42:24,070 --> 01:42:25,500
I'm not asking you about that, though.

1553
01:42:27,610 --> 01:42:31,210
I don't want to pick someone on this show for a light reason...

1554
01:42:31,380 --> 01:42:33,379
like having butterflies...

1555
01:42:33,380 --> 01:42:36,850
and feeling romantic toward him. I'm considering more factors.

1556
01:42:37,380 --> 01:42:38,520
So...

1557
01:42:40,320 --> 01:42:43,190
But talking about this...

1558
01:42:45,220 --> 01:42:46,230
What is it?

1559
01:42:49,560 --> 01:42:52,930
What I really wanted to discuss was...

1560
01:42:53,230 --> 01:42:56,170
our reality. Given the nature of the subject,

1561
01:42:56,340 --> 01:43:00,240
I was really hesitant to bring that up.

1562
01:43:03,010 --> 01:43:04,410
My gosh. Come on.

1563
01:43:05,540 --> 01:43:06,580
What is it? Tell me.

1564
01:43:09,080 --> 01:43:11,020
Before we played the game of truth or dare,

1565
01:43:11,920 --> 01:43:14,090
I asked Min Kyung why they broke up and she told me...

1566
01:43:14,490 --> 01:43:17,990
Yoo Sik wasn't planning a future with her.

1567
01:43:18,460 --> 01:43:21,160
She said that he wasn't interested in marriage.

1568
01:43:21,560 --> 01:43:23,629
People might think we can talk about this...

1569
01:43:23,630 --> 01:43:26,329
once we finish filming the show...

1570
01:43:26,330 --> 01:43:28,770
when we are in private.

1571
01:43:28,970 --> 01:43:30,070
But...

1572
01:43:31,070 --> 01:43:34,369
personally, marriage has been in the picture for me.

1573
01:43:34,370 --> 01:43:37,340
So I wanted to hear his stance about marriage.

1574
01:43:40,210 --> 01:43:42,349
I'll tell you what's been on my mind.

1575
01:43:42,350 --> 01:43:43,620
I'll just share it.

1576
01:43:45,480 --> 01:43:49,090
I was completely set on picking you at the end.

1577
01:43:49,260 --> 01:43:50,420
At one point, that's what I thought.

1578
01:43:50,990 --> 01:43:52,460
But...

1579
01:43:53,260 --> 01:43:56,030
Seung Yong is doing everything he can to change my mind.

1580
01:43:56,660 --> 01:44:00,670
He talked to me about our reality and future.

1581
01:44:00,700 --> 01:44:02,200
He and I...

1582
01:44:03,040 --> 01:44:05,670
were getting ready...

1583
01:44:07,870 --> 01:44:09,239
- for marriage.
- Okay.

1584
01:44:09,240 --> 01:44:12,909
Anyway, marriage had been in the picture for us.

1585
01:44:12,910 --> 01:44:16,250
But we broke up while getting ready for marriage.

1586
01:44:17,650 --> 01:44:18,720
So...

1587
01:44:19,450 --> 01:44:21,990
when he mentioned those things again,

1588
01:44:22,090 --> 01:44:25,219
I had a lot to think about.

1589
01:44:25,220 --> 01:44:29,060
But I wasn't sure if I should ask you about this.

1590
01:44:33,070 --> 01:44:37,169
You might have different values from me.

1591
01:44:37,170 --> 01:44:38,170
Okay.

1592
01:44:40,670 --> 01:44:42,479
What values? Like my values on marriage?

1593
01:44:42,480 --> 01:44:43,809
You might not believe in marriage.

1594
01:44:43,810 --> 01:44:45,679
- Do I not believe in marriage?
- Right.

1595
01:44:45,680 --> 01:44:46,850
That's what you want to know?

1596
01:44:50,080 --> 01:44:52,890
Before we played the game yesterday,

1597
01:44:53,390 --> 01:44:54,949
I asked Min Kyung.

1598
01:44:54,950 --> 01:44:58,060
I told her about my dilemma.

1599
01:44:58,420 --> 01:44:59,629
You talked to Min Kyung?

1600
01:44:59,630 --> 01:45:01,990
- I asked her.
- You asked her yesterday?

1601
01:45:02,460 --> 01:45:05,230
I asked her yesterday before we played truth or dare.

1602
01:45:06,300 --> 01:45:07,300
I got it.

1603
01:45:08,170 --> 01:45:09,239
- I asked her.
- You...

1604
01:45:09,240 --> 01:45:11,269
- You're going to break your nails.
- I told her...

1605
01:45:11,270 --> 01:45:13,270
- what was bothering me.
- Okay.

1606
01:45:14,570 --> 01:45:18,280
I asked her if marriage was the reason you guys broke up.

1607
01:45:19,710 --> 01:45:22,009
She made it sound like it was.

1608
01:45:22,010 --> 01:45:25,120
(His ex and his new flame talked about the future.)

1609
01:45:26,850 --> 01:45:28,020
I can see why this could be a dilemma.

1610
01:45:31,020 --> 01:45:32,659
Min Kyung asked me yesterday about the future...

1611
01:45:32,660 --> 01:45:34,460
- I had pictured for us.
- Yes.

1612
01:45:35,160 --> 01:45:37,330
If I were ready in every aspect...

1613
01:45:38,130 --> 01:45:39,869
and could fully provide for her,

1614
01:45:39,870 --> 01:45:41,570
so she wouldn't have to lift a finger...

1615
01:45:43,170 --> 01:45:44,440
to have a happy marriage,

1616
01:45:45,370 --> 01:45:46,970
then ultimately,

1617
01:45:48,770 --> 01:45:52,380
I would want to marry her. That's what I thought.

1618
01:45:53,710 --> 01:45:56,979
So if I'm not capable of making someone happy...

1619
01:45:56,980 --> 01:46:00,450
Let's say I don't have enough to make her happy.

1620
01:46:02,050 --> 01:46:05,790
I'll never mention marriage to her.

1621
01:46:06,730 --> 01:46:09,959
That's why you said that you had never told her...

1622
01:46:09,960 --> 01:46:12,330
what she wanted to hear.

1623
01:46:13,070 --> 01:46:15,600
- Was that along the same line?
- I said that?

1624
01:46:15,870 --> 01:46:17,300
- Yes.
- That's true.

1625
01:46:17,900 --> 01:46:20,140
- I never even joked about it.
- That's what I figured.

1626
01:46:20,510 --> 01:46:23,210
When it came to marriage and serious subjects like that,

1627
01:46:23,540 --> 01:46:25,580
I had never said things I didn't mean.

1628
01:46:26,910 --> 01:46:29,080
Honestly, making such a promise...

1629
01:46:30,420 --> 01:46:32,420
would make me irresponsible...

1630
01:46:33,090 --> 01:46:35,350
when I'm not even capable...

1631
01:46:36,220 --> 01:46:37,990
of making anyone happy.

1632
01:46:39,690 --> 01:46:42,800
But I didn't know we'd have a deep conversation about this.

1633
01:46:45,800 --> 01:46:46,830
I told you.

1634
01:46:48,900 --> 01:46:49,900
What?

1635
01:46:49,901 --> 01:46:52,070
Make a decision that will make you happy.

1636
01:46:53,340 --> 01:46:56,180
Make a decision that will make me happy? How will I know that?

1637
01:46:58,080 --> 01:46:59,110
Just do that.

1638
01:46:59,750 --> 01:47:02,250
I told you I wanted you to be happy.

1639
01:47:04,080 --> 01:47:07,149
I gave you a 3-leaf clover for a reason, not a 4-leaf clover.

1640
01:47:07,150 --> 01:47:10,290
(She has a lot on her mind after hearing his answer.)

1641
01:47:12,360 --> 01:47:16,060
Of course, I want to make a decision I won't regret.

1642
01:47:16,230 --> 01:47:17,300
Right.

1643
01:47:23,640 --> 01:47:24,840
I really don't know.

1644
01:47:25,400 --> 01:47:28,009
I'm interested in Yoo Sik.

1645
01:47:28,010 --> 01:47:29,680
But I have to consider...

1646
01:47:32,540 --> 01:47:33,910
the reality too.

1647
01:47:34,610 --> 01:47:38,350
It gave me a chance to think seriously about him...

1648
01:47:39,080 --> 01:47:41,350
once again.

1649
01:47:45,860 --> 01:47:47,830
- We should get going.
- What?

1650
01:47:48,430 --> 01:47:49,930
- You want to get going?
- Yes.

1651
01:47:54,200 --> 01:47:55,500
This is crazy.

1652
01:48:00,970 --> 01:48:02,039
Let's go.

1653
01:48:02,040 --> 01:48:08,050
(Their feelings become a tangled mess before the final decision.)

1654
01:48:10,820 --> 01:48:12,019
- Why...
- My gosh.

1655
01:48:12,020 --> 01:48:14,589
His answer didn't fully address...

1656
01:48:14,590 --> 01:48:15,719
- Hyeon Ji's concerns.
- No.

1657
01:48:15,720 --> 01:48:16,859
- It didn't.
- It didn't clear them up.

1658
01:48:16,860 --> 01:48:17,889
- Right?
- It was really vague.

1659
01:48:17,890 --> 01:48:19,729
Saying... "Make a decision that will make you happy."

1660
01:48:19,730 --> 01:48:21,929
- Right.
- I don't know what will happen.

1661
01:48:21,930 --> 01:48:24,699
- My gosh. This is...
- I'm so confused.

1662
01:48:24,700 --> 01:48:26,430
Their conversation ended on a vague note.

1663
01:48:35,210 --> 01:48:38,580
(Baek Hyun arrives at the secret date spot.)

1664
01:48:41,450 --> 01:48:44,950
Since it was a date after my date with Hyeon Ji,

1665
01:48:45,150 --> 01:48:47,850
I was feeling down on the secret date.

1666
01:48:50,220 --> 01:48:52,420
That bothered me quite a bit.

1667
01:48:54,390 --> 01:48:56,730
It was our last date together.

1668
01:48:58,260 --> 01:48:59,499
I wanted her to be happy.

1669
01:48:59,500 --> 01:49:02,469
But I didn't know how to do that since I was feeling down.

1670
01:49:02,470 --> 01:49:04,070
I was only thinking about that.

1671
01:49:09,840 --> 01:49:11,679
- You're here.
- Good evening.

1672
01:49:11,680 --> 01:49:12,809
Good evening.

1673
01:49:12,810 --> 01:49:14,510
(Yun Nyeong and Baek Hyun's secret date)

1674
01:49:14,610 --> 01:49:16,250
- Did you wait long?
- No.

1675
01:49:17,620 --> 01:49:18,980
Your outfit looks cute.

1676
01:49:19,150 --> 01:49:21,020
- Cute, right? It's a denim outfit.
- Yes.

1677
01:49:24,120 --> 01:49:25,220
What did you do?

1678
01:49:25,320 --> 01:49:26,360
What did I do today?

1679
01:49:27,460 --> 01:49:29,559
I went on a date with my ex and rested at the house.

1680
01:49:29,560 --> 01:49:30,930
What did you do on the date?

1681
01:49:31,400 --> 01:49:32,899
We just had a meal.

1682
01:49:32,900 --> 01:49:33,930
Really?

1683
01:49:36,400 --> 01:49:37,440
Did you have fun?

1684
01:49:38,470 --> 01:49:39,710
- Fun?
- Yes.

1685
01:49:41,470 --> 01:49:42,470
Well, you know...

1686
01:49:43,640 --> 01:49:44,640
You want me to be honest?

1687
01:49:48,210 --> 01:49:49,350
It was a bit sad.

1688
01:49:53,020 --> 01:49:54,490
It was sad.

1689
01:49:56,190 --> 01:49:57,690
It was your last date with her.

1690
01:50:00,030 --> 01:50:01,060
It felt weird.

1691
01:50:05,260 --> 01:50:06,300
Is that so?

1692
01:50:09,070 --> 01:50:10,970
Gosh, that looks so good.

1693
01:50:11,940 --> 01:50:15,240
(The food they ordered is served.)

1694
01:50:16,380 --> 01:50:18,279
- Thank you for the meal.
- Enjoy.

1695
01:50:18,280 --> 01:50:19,410
I will.

1696
01:50:25,650 --> 01:50:27,050
What did you and Jae Hyeong talk about?

1697
01:50:29,690 --> 01:50:32,060
We mostly talked about the old days.

1698
01:50:32,320 --> 01:50:35,430
It was our first date on the show.

1699
01:50:37,460 --> 01:50:39,500
I didn't think Hyeon Ji would go on a date with both of us.

1700
01:50:40,070 --> 01:50:41,370
I thought she'd go on a date with just one of us.

1701
01:50:42,230 --> 01:50:46,539
But luckily, she went on a date with both of us.

1702
01:50:46,540 --> 01:50:47,540
Okay.

1703
01:50:50,580 --> 01:50:52,539
- It was nice.
- It's nice you got to say goodbye.

1704
01:50:52,540 --> 01:50:53,610
- Right. It was good.
- Yes.

1705
01:50:54,710 --> 01:50:56,479
But I'm very happy.

1706
01:50:56,480 --> 01:50:59,590
It means we did our best.

1707
01:50:59,950 --> 01:51:01,920
- That's true.
- I'm very happy.

1708
01:51:04,590 --> 01:51:06,330
Now you can hang out with me.

1709
01:51:10,300 --> 01:51:12,300
You said your goodbyes.

1710
01:51:20,340 --> 01:51:22,740
Do you feel confused?

1711
01:51:34,020 --> 01:51:35,350
I think I kind of...

1712
01:51:38,690 --> 01:51:39,790
feel confused.

1713
01:51:48,970 --> 01:51:51,770
- Do you feel confused?
- Me?

1714
01:51:52,940 --> 01:51:54,170
Not me.

1715
01:51:59,340 --> 01:52:02,480
(The dessert arrives.)

1716
01:52:05,050 --> 01:52:06,290
Did you get some sleep last night?

1717
01:52:06,890 --> 01:52:09,020
Yes, I did.

1718
01:52:09,090 --> 01:52:10,619
I went to bed as soon as I went in.

1719
01:52:10,620 --> 01:52:11,820
- Really?
- Yes.

1720
01:52:12,360 --> 01:52:13,530
Did you sleep well?

1721
01:52:14,760 --> 01:52:16,530
I barely slept last night.

1722
01:52:16,800 --> 01:52:19,030
I had to wake up early.

1723
01:52:19,460 --> 01:52:21,830
But I took a nap for over five hours today.

1724
01:52:22,470 --> 01:52:24,570
I slept. It wasn't a nap.

1725
01:52:26,240 --> 01:52:28,870
I had a dream. It was my first time dreaming since I came here.

1726
01:52:29,070 --> 01:52:30,410
What did you dream about?

1727
01:52:31,440 --> 01:52:32,510
Tell me.

1728
01:52:32,610 --> 01:52:34,480
It was a strange dream.

1729
01:52:35,510 --> 01:52:38,749
Do you really want to hear about it? It was such a strange dream.

1730
01:52:38,750 --> 01:52:41,390
- Yes.
- Hyeon Ji was next to me.

1731
01:52:42,520 --> 01:52:47,430
Someone named a sorrow fairy appeared.

1732
01:52:48,360 --> 01:52:50,730
I don't know. I guess I was sad?

1733
01:52:51,730 --> 01:52:54,300
So the sorrow fairy appeared...

1734
01:52:56,070 --> 01:52:59,640
and gave me a hug.

1735
01:53:00,570 --> 01:53:02,369
She told me to cry if I was sad,

1736
01:53:02,370 --> 01:53:04,279
so I cried so much in my dream.

1737
01:53:04,280 --> 01:53:06,350
- You did?
- When I was taking a nap.

1738
01:53:08,050 --> 01:53:09,050
It was such a strange dream.

1739
01:53:09,051 --> 01:53:11,379
Hyeon Ji was there, and the sorrow fairy too?

1740
01:53:11,380 --> 01:53:12,989
Yes. Hyeon Ji was just watching me.

1741
01:53:12,990 --> 01:53:14,790
And I was hugging the sorrow fairy.

1742
01:53:17,260 --> 01:53:19,190
- I cried.
- You did?

1743
01:53:19,790 --> 01:53:21,630
It felt strange.

1744
01:53:28,800 --> 01:53:31,600
It was strange to have such a dream.

1745
01:53:34,110 --> 01:53:35,970
I hated that situation.

1746
01:53:36,210 --> 01:53:38,379
I expected Yun Nyeong...

1747
01:53:38,380 --> 01:53:39,780
to see my emotional state.

1748
01:53:40,280 --> 01:53:42,050
I couldn't help it.

1749
01:53:42,510 --> 01:53:44,420
I couldn't pretend to be excited...

1750
01:53:44,580 --> 01:53:46,490
when I was down.

1751
01:53:48,120 --> 01:53:50,290
I was worried about Hyeon Ji.

1752
01:53:56,730 --> 01:53:57,800
This.

1753
01:54:00,170 --> 01:54:02,499
My bracelet?

1754
01:54:02,500 --> 01:54:04,670
(The bracelet Baek Hyun gave her)

1755
01:54:09,140 --> 01:54:10,610
Hyeon Ji asked me about it.

1756
01:54:10,780 --> 01:54:12,480
"You gave Yun Nyeong a bracelet."

1757
01:54:18,220 --> 01:54:19,350
Do you want me to help you put it on?

1758
01:54:21,020 --> 01:54:23,090
You're okay? Okay.

1759
01:54:25,060 --> 01:54:26,429
- I'm okay.
- Okay.

1760
01:54:26,430 --> 01:54:28,160
- I'm okay.
- Okay.

1761
01:54:28,390 --> 01:54:29,560
Is that how you say it in Japanese?

1762
01:54:30,160 --> 01:54:31,160
Yes.

1763
01:54:34,370 --> 01:54:37,870
He seemed to be worried about Hyeon Ji.

1764
01:54:38,070 --> 01:54:40,609
He might have experienced an emotional change.

1765
01:54:40,610 --> 01:54:42,739
What if he chooses his ex over me?

1766
01:54:42,740 --> 01:54:46,180
I was a little worried...

1767
01:54:47,210 --> 01:54:48,250
about that.

1768
01:54:50,280 --> 01:54:53,290
Let's go. That was good.

1769
01:54:54,850 --> 01:54:58,460
(Their last date is over.)

1770
01:54:58,890 --> 01:55:00,389
- She returned the bracelet.
- Yes.

1771
01:55:00,390 --> 01:55:03,359
She was probably planning to give it back to him.

1772
01:55:03,360 --> 01:55:05,029
She doesn't look that good.

1773
01:55:05,030 --> 01:55:06,769
- He's too honest.
- Yes, he's too honest.

1774
01:55:06,770 --> 01:55:09,529
He's unnecessarily honest. It's okay...

1775
01:55:09,530 --> 01:55:11,869
- to be sad...
- Wouldn't the sorrow fairy...

1776
01:55:11,870 --> 01:55:12,870
tell him not to say it?

1777
01:55:12,871 --> 01:55:15,609
About his dream, that's his subconsciousness.

1778
01:55:15,610 --> 01:55:16,810
Right.

1779
01:55:18,480 --> 01:55:19,540
It's tomorrow.

1780
01:55:20,250 --> 01:55:22,150
I know. It's tomorrow.

1781
01:55:22,910 --> 01:55:24,720
Now that it's tomorrow,

1782
01:55:25,420 --> 01:55:26,690
I'm getting a lot on my mind.

1783
01:55:29,860 --> 01:55:31,890
I have a lot of regrets.

1784
01:55:36,260 --> 01:55:38,330
We're making our final decision tomorrow.

1785
01:55:38,900 --> 01:55:41,000
Are you going to talk to Ji Hyeon again?

1786
01:55:42,900 --> 01:55:45,400
I don't know if I should.

1787
01:55:45,670 --> 01:55:47,740
- I'm not going to.
- Is it better that way?

1788
01:55:48,340 --> 01:55:50,509
I didn't talk to her that much,

1789
01:55:50,510 --> 01:55:52,480
but I think I said everything I had to.

1790
01:55:55,510 --> 01:55:57,450
I don't know what's there to say.

1791
01:56:00,050 --> 01:56:01,090
So...

1792
01:56:01,320 --> 01:56:02,719
I've done what I could,

1793
01:56:02,720 --> 01:56:05,120
