- What were you doing?
- Where have you been?

1800
01:56:20,670 --> 01:56:22,109
I had something delicious.

1801
01:56:22,110 --> 01:56:23,540
- You had something delicious?
- Yes.

1802
01:56:24,310 --> 01:56:26,080
Did you have something delicious alone again?

1803
01:56:26,550 --> 01:56:28,450
We're starving.

1804
01:56:30,380 --> 01:56:32,279
Why didn't you accept my date?

1805
01:56:32,280 --> 01:56:34,419
- Your date?
- Yes. I asked you.

1806
01:56:34,420 --> 01:56:35,890
- That's ridiculous.
- Really?

1807
01:56:36,090 --> 01:56:37,420
- Yes.
- Me too.

1808
01:56:37,490 --> 01:56:38,560
Hey.

1809
01:56:38,920 --> 01:56:41,529
Hey. I'm so popular.

1810
01:56:41,530 --> 01:56:43,499
- Why?
- They all asked me to go on a date.

1811
01:56:43,500 --> 01:56:45,729
I wanted to eat something delicious before I go.

1812
01:56:45,730 --> 01:56:47,569
- Really?
- I wanted to take you out.

1813
01:56:47,570 --> 01:56:48,630
Really?

1814
01:56:49,230 --> 01:56:50,770
Where is everyone?

1815
01:56:51,000 --> 01:56:53,069
Everyone? Some of them are in their rooms.

1816
01:56:53,070 --> 01:56:54,070
Really?

1817
01:56:55,170 --> 01:56:58,010
(Yellow Room: Ji Hyeon and Hyeon Ji's room)

1818
01:56:58,680 --> 01:57:00,780
- Hyeon Ji.
- Yes.

1819
01:57:00,980 --> 01:57:02,110
Did you have fun?

1820
01:57:03,320 --> 01:57:04,780
Today...

1821
01:57:06,380 --> 01:57:08,290
Today? Fun...

1822
01:57:09,490 --> 01:57:13,059
Have you made up your mind? It's tomorrow.

1823
01:57:13,060 --> 01:57:15,529
My mind? Yes, I have.

1824
01:57:15,530 --> 01:57:16,630
You have?

1825
01:57:16,830 --> 01:57:18,860
I think I need to talk to him more.

1826
01:57:19,430 --> 01:57:20,499
You've made up your mind,

1827
01:57:20,500 --> 01:57:21,970
- I...
- but you still need to talk to him?

1828
01:57:22,500 --> 01:57:25,440
- What's going on?
- There wasn't enough time.

1829
01:57:25,940 --> 01:57:28,439
I got all kinds of thoughts.

1830
01:57:28,440 --> 01:57:31,340
You must be a very careful person.

1831
01:57:31,910 --> 01:57:34,879
Yes, because depending on my decision,

1832
01:57:34,880 --> 01:57:38,420
I'm going to lose someone.

1833
01:57:39,020 --> 01:57:41,749
No wonder you're careful, and you get a lot on your mind.

1834
01:57:41,750 --> 01:57:42,820
Right.

1835
01:57:44,120 --> 01:57:45,960
Seriously.

1836
01:57:48,390 --> 01:57:52,200
(They're stirred before the last decision.)

1837
01:57:52,560 --> 01:57:55,830
If it's only about dating, it might be easier.

1838
01:57:55,930 --> 01:57:58,199
But she can't stop thinking about marriage.

1839
01:57:58,200 --> 01:57:59,299
- What if she ends up...
- Seung Yong...

1840
01:57:59,300 --> 01:58:00,409
choosing Seung Yong?

1841
01:58:00,410 --> 01:58:02,839
Did make a big move.

1842
01:58:02,840 --> 01:58:04,339
Don't let this night go away.

1843
01:58:04,340 --> 01:58:06,079
It's not over yet.

1844
01:58:06,080 --> 01:58:07,710
Aside from the date with an ex.

1845
01:58:09,450 --> 01:58:11,720
(Blue Room: Won Kyu and Yoo Sik's room)

1846
01:58:18,820 --> 01:58:19,960
My goodness.

1847
01:58:21,060 --> 01:58:24,759
I had something to ask.

1848
01:58:24,760 --> 01:58:25,800
Now?

1849
01:58:29,370 --> 01:58:31,599
(Hyeon Ji requests to talk.)

1850
01:58:31,600 --> 01:58:32,670
Gosh.

1851
01:58:35,710 --> 01:58:38,940
I asked you before...

1852
01:58:39,340 --> 01:58:42,110
if you ever made the person you liked...

1853
01:58:42,550 --> 01:58:44,449
certain.

1854
01:58:44,450 --> 01:58:46,050
During the truth or dare?

1855
01:58:47,750 --> 01:58:49,090
I meant...

1856
01:58:49,490 --> 01:58:52,920
that I never mentioned about my final decision.

1857
01:58:55,730 --> 01:58:56,730
What?

1858
01:58:58,000 --> 01:59:00,829
I'm bothered by what you said.

1859
01:59:00,830 --> 01:59:01,870
What do you mean?

1860
01:59:02,330 --> 01:59:03,400
It's just...

1861
01:59:04,040 --> 01:59:07,340
The decision tomorrow...

1862
01:59:10,080 --> 01:59:12,540
I shouldn't have mentioned that.

1863
01:59:15,450 --> 01:59:17,380
Or am I thinking too much?

1864
01:59:18,450 --> 01:59:20,890
You're just trying to be careful about your decision, aren't you?

1865
01:59:22,020 --> 01:59:23,660
I should be careful about my decision.

1866
01:59:24,860 --> 01:59:26,220
Are you still thinking?

1867
01:59:27,030 --> 01:59:28,690
Then go to bed.

1868
01:59:31,360 --> 01:59:32,560
Do you have anything to say?

1869
01:59:32,860 --> 01:59:34,170
Do I have anything to say?

1870
01:59:34,600 --> 01:59:36,170
What can I say?

1871
01:59:38,840 --> 01:59:39,939
It was sad.

1872
01:59:39,940 --> 01:59:41,410
(Orange Room: Ji Hyeon's room)

1873
01:59:41,670 --> 01:59:43,010
How are you feeling?

1874
01:59:46,280 --> 01:59:48,710
It's kind of relieving.

1875
01:59:48,850 --> 01:59:51,079
We didn't get to talk a lot.

1876
01:59:51,080 --> 01:59:52,180
But today,

1877
01:59:52,980 --> 01:59:54,420
I thought...

1878
01:59:56,250 --> 01:59:59,760
I shouldn't say much.

1879
02:00:00,530 --> 02:00:02,290
- Why?
- After coming here.

1880
02:00:03,400 --> 02:00:06,199
Basically, I'm repeating...

1881
02:00:06,200 --> 02:00:07,970
myself.

1882
02:00:08,830 --> 02:00:11,399
I've been telling her...

1883
02:00:11,400 --> 02:00:13,610
about how I could change.

1884
02:00:14,970 --> 02:00:17,279
Aside from that, all I could say is...

1885
02:00:17,280 --> 02:00:19,810
just emotional stuff.

1886
02:00:21,080 --> 02:00:23,209
But to say,

1887
02:00:23,210 --> 02:00:26,689
"I like you so much. I love you,"

1888
02:00:26,690 --> 02:00:28,350
in a situation like this,

1889
02:00:29,420 --> 02:00:32,590
it'll be strange, and she won't accept that anyway.

1890
02:00:33,360 --> 02:00:35,960
I think I've said enough...

1891
02:00:36,560 --> 02:00:38,200
of what I could say rationally.

1892
02:00:39,700 --> 02:00:42,830
No more deep conversation is...

1893
02:00:43,540 --> 02:00:45,370
needed anyway.

1894
02:00:46,340 --> 02:00:49,440
I'm kind of nervous about tomorrow.

1895
02:00:50,710 --> 02:00:52,510
I'm actually kind of scared.

1896
02:00:54,710 --> 02:00:57,350
If I were to take responsibility...

1897
02:00:58,020 --> 02:01:00,450
for this decision,

1898
02:01:02,490 --> 02:01:04,120
it's not easy...

1899
02:01:04,720 --> 02:01:07,660
to decide our reunion.

1900
02:01:10,030 --> 02:01:11,130
That's true.

1901
02:01:13,060 --> 02:01:15,199
In terms...

1902
02:01:15,200 --> 02:01:18,000
of the final decision tomorrow,

1903
02:01:19,170 --> 02:01:21,640
I'm going to think carefully to the end.

1904
02:01:24,880 --> 02:01:30,980
(They contemplate even more on their final night.)

1905
02:01:33,750 --> 02:01:34,850
Think carefully.

1906
02:01:46,900 --> 02:01:48,700
Have you made up your mind?

1907
02:01:48,870 --> 02:01:50,569
Yes, I have.

1908
02:01:50,570 --> 02:01:51,740
(Purple Room: Min Kyung and Yun Nyeong's room)

1909
02:01:52,070 --> 02:01:54,370
Whatever it's going to be, it breaks my heart.

1910
02:01:54,470 --> 02:01:55,940
It breaks your heart?

1911
02:01:58,710 --> 02:02:01,049
Yoo Sik, that jerk.

1912
02:02:01,050 --> 02:02:05,050
He's good at making people desperate.

1913
02:02:06,220 --> 02:02:07,250
Gosh.

1914
02:02:09,490 --> 02:02:10,520
Gosh.

1915
02:02:11,620 --> 02:02:13,689
This is what happens when you put the brightest person...

1916
02:02:13,690 --> 02:02:15,660
and the darkest person together in one room.

1917
02:02:15,930 --> 02:02:17,130
That's us.

1918
02:02:17,900 --> 02:02:19,000
I never stop chattering.

1919
02:02:20,030 --> 02:02:21,169
- No.
- Seriously.

1920
02:02:21,170 --> 02:02:22,799
- No.
- I was kind of...

1921
02:02:22,800 --> 02:02:25,399
stressed today.

1922
02:02:25,400 --> 02:02:26,539
- Today?
- Yes.

1923
02:02:26,540 --> 02:02:29,170
- Why?
- I don't know. It's just that...

1924
02:02:30,210 --> 02:02:33,140
On a date, Baek Hyun...

1925
02:02:34,180 --> 02:02:36,750
Anyway, he went on a date with his ex today.

1926
02:02:37,350 --> 02:02:38,649
- Yes.
- He said...

1927
02:02:38,650 --> 02:02:41,749
he'd be swayed...

1928
02:02:41,750 --> 02:02:45,619
if his ex tried.

1929
02:02:45,620 --> 02:02:48,189
That kind of bothered me.

1930
02:02:48,190 --> 02:02:51,460
I thought, "What if he really gets swayed?"

1931
02:02:51,860 --> 02:02:53,129
I doubt it.

1932
02:02:53,130 --> 02:02:55,299
He was so certain...

1933
02:02:55,300 --> 02:02:57,270
to say it.

1934
02:02:57,800 --> 02:03:01,069
That means they had a very deep relationship.

1935
02:03:01,070 --> 02:03:02,669
And when I listen to him,

1936
02:03:02,670 --> 02:03:04,310
it sounds like they did have a deep relationship.

1937
02:03:06,180 --> 02:03:07,379
- Of course...
- No one here had...

1938
02:03:07,380 --> 02:03:08,609
a light relationship.

1939
02:03:08,610 --> 02:03:10,049
Everyone had a deep relationship.

1940
02:03:10,050 --> 02:03:13,350
Yes, but...

1941
02:03:13,890 --> 02:03:14,950
that...

1942
02:03:16,990 --> 02:03:19,620
- It bothers you.
- Yes, it bothers me.

1943
02:03:19,960 --> 02:03:21,529
He might have a change of heart...

1944
02:03:21,530 --> 02:03:25,060
after the date today.

1945
02:03:25,830 --> 02:03:29,730
That kind of bothers me.

1946
02:03:32,440 --> 02:03:33,470
Right.

1947
02:03:34,240 --> 02:03:37,080
Sometimes I can't hide my emotion because of that.

1948
02:03:38,510 --> 02:03:40,850
And Baek Hyun...

1949
02:03:42,550 --> 02:03:43,719
I don't know.

1950
02:03:43,720 --> 02:03:45,679
He talks about Hyeon Ji.

1951
02:03:45,680 --> 02:03:47,189
He said he had a dream last night.

1952
02:03:47,190 --> 02:03:48,919
Hyeon Ji was next to him.

1953
02:03:48,920 --> 02:03:51,860
And a sorrow fairy soothed him in her arms.

1954
02:03:53,390 --> 02:03:55,329
- What?
- I was like, "Okay."

1955
02:03:55,330 --> 02:03:57,259
He had a very weird dream.

1956
02:03:57,260 --> 02:03:58,359
I know. I was like, "Okay."

1957
02:03:58,360 --> 02:04:00,329
Then he talked about Hyeon Ji again.

1958
02:04:00,330 --> 02:04:03,129
"Strangely enough, Hyeon Ji had Japanese currency."

1959
02:04:03,130 --> 02:04:05,439
"Why does she have it? Isn't that interesting?"

1960
02:04:05,440 --> 02:04:07,609
- I wasn't that curious.
- Right.

1961
02:04:07,610 --> 02:04:09,669
It wasn't the first time.

1962
02:04:09,670 --> 02:04:13,139
He said he dreamed about her. He did this and that with her.

1963
02:04:13,140 --> 02:04:15,210
And he kept talking about her.

1964
02:04:20,080 --> 02:04:22,949
I couldn't go,

1965
02:04:22,950 --> 02:04:24,360
"Oh, really?"

1966
02:04:25,290 --> 02:04:27,290
Right. That's upsetting.

1967
02:04:30,800 --> 02:04:32,800
I don't know.

1968
02:04:33,970 --> 02:04:37,040
- I don't know.
- What do you mean?

1969
02:04:37,340 --> 02:04:40,470
He's certain, and he's so nice to you.

1970
02:04:42,610 --> 02:04:44,810
But he might be swayed.

1971
02:04:45,280 --> 02:04:46,340
Right.

1972
02:04:47,350 --> 02:04:50,480
But you won't have to worry.

1973
02:04:50,920 --> 02:04:53,080
You're a very charming person.

1974
02:04:53,480 --> 02:04:57,890
Baek Hyun has no reason not to choose you.

1975
02:05:00,430 --> 02:05:03,030
We never know until it's over.

1976
02:05:10,570 --> 02:05:11,640
Today,

1977
02:05:14,570 --> 02:05:16,070
while we were eating,

1978
02:05:19,910 --> 02:05:21,850
Yoo Sik cried so much.

1979
02:05:25,780 --> 02:05:27,020
He cried so much?

1980
02:05:30,860 --> 02:05:34,360
He and I both cried so much.

1981
02:05:37,060 --> 02:05:38,130
Both of you?

1982
02:05:40,800 --> 02:05:41,900
Yes.

1983
02:05:50,640 --> 02:05:53,010
- It was crazy.
- Don't cry.

1984
02:05:54,510 --> 02:05:56,380
I shouldn't cry.

1985
02:06:02,090 --> 02:06:04,060
I'll leave water here.

1986
02:06:09,330 --> 02:06:12,600
- I cried so much.
- You cried so much?

1987
02:06:31,820 --> 02:06:33,850
I'm so upset.

1988
02:06:39,760 --> 02:06:40,790
Gosh.

1989
02:06:47,200 --> 02:06:51,200
I shouldn't cry. I cried so much today.

1990
02:06:53,640 --> 02:06:55,810
Gosh.

1991
02:06:57,940 --> 02:06:59,410
This is so hard.

1992
02:07:04,220 --> 02:07:05,820
It breaks my heart.

1993
02:07:09,250 --> 02:07:11,590
If he chooses Hyeon Ji,

1994
02:07:13,830 --> 02:07:16,030
that means he has no regrets...

1995
02:07:16,590 --> 02:07:17,830
about letting me go.

1996
02:07:19,360 --> 02:07:21,300
I'm scared that might happen.

1997
02:07:24,800 --> 02:07:27,710
Honestly, I said I didn't care in front of him.

1998
02:07:30,170 --> 02:07:31,580
I pretended to be okay.

1999
02:07:32,680 --> 02:07:34,280
But I'm not okay at all.

2000
02:07:35,980 --> 02:07:37,650
I'm in so much pain.

2001
02:07:45,590 --> 02:07:48,930
(EXchange 4)

2002
02:07:49,190 --> 02:07:51,659
You tried to be firm...

2003
02:07:51,660 --> 02:07:53,259
about Yun Nyeong here.

2004
02:07:53,260 --> 02:07:54,300
Yes.

2005
02:07:54,500 --> 02:07:56,700
And why are you suddenly doing this?

2006
02:07:57,500 --> 02:07:59,270
When I went on a date with my ex yesterday...

2007
02:08:01,470 --> 02:08:02,470
Yesterday...

2008
02:08:03,340 --> 02:08:04,740
You didn't mean it, did you?

2009
02:08:08,880 --> 02:08:10,679
If either one of us pushes it,

2010
02:08:10,680 --> 02:08:12,750
I know we'd get back together.

2011
02:08:13,220 --> 02:08:16,049
(Between the ex...)

2012
02:08:16,050 --> 02:08:18,619
(and the new girl)

2013
02:08:18,620 --> 02:08:20,590
(The end of the crossroad)

2014
02:08:20,930 --> 02:08:24,630
Actually, it's unpredictable.

2015
02:08:26,460 --> 02:08:28,730
I can't stop thinking...

2016
02:08:29,430 --> 02:08:31,240
about the disappointing and hurtful moments.

2017
02:08:32,270 --> 02:08:33,340
Why are you crying?

2018
02:08:35,410 --> 02:08:37,780
I don't want them to repeat again.

2019
02:08:38,010 --> 02:08:40,110
Without an excuse...

2020
02:08:40,650 --> 02:08:42,350
(I'm sorry.)

2021
02:08:42,610 --> 02:08:45,780
It felt so strange. I had a lot on my mind.

2022
02:08:46,280 --> 02:08:49,550
(It could be the end.)

2023
02:08:50,520 --> 02:08:52,890
I'll be okay with any choice you make.

2024
02:08:53,590 --> 02:08:56,630
It feels like we're going back to that time when I'm with you.

2025
02:08:57,160 --> 02:09:01,069
I know how much we meant to each other.

2026
02:09:01,070 --> 02:09:03,700
We know each other the best.

2027
02:09:04,770 --> 02:09:08,670
(Final decision, D-day)
